m should be performed as in South Korea and Japan," he said after the dialogue and socialization of financial service authorities bill in Jakarta yesterday. \par \par \uc2  But Anwar cautioned government and BI had yet to decide when the plan to reduce bank collateral take place. "This is just a plan, so don't exaggerate it because it was being reviewed." \par \par \uc2  He said blanket guarantee scheme for all funds at banks today had become expensive costs for the government. "The blanket guarantee burden is expensive and we all should pay for it. To alleviate government's burden, collateral should be reduced gradually." \par \par \uc2  According to Anwar, because confidence toward banks has been improving, banks and customers need not worry. "Banks need not fear that their customers fund would go out from banking system." \par \par \uc2  Based on data of \b \highlight22\uc2 Bank Indonesia\b0 \highlight\uc2 , total banks third party fund during the last three months were increasing. Banks third party's total fund stood at Rp783.4 trillion, then higher up to Rp785.1 trillion on April 2002, to become Rp787 trillion on May. \par \par \uc2  Governor of \b \highlight22\uc2 Bank Indonesia\b0 \highlight\uc2  Syahril Sabirin at the same location said press news about a case was exaggerating, in contrary to the reality. \par \par \uc2  According to him the scrap would be implemented gradually, little by little, to finally be handed over to saving collateral agency. "So it is not scrapped totally," he said. \par \par \uc2  BI, Syahril continued, has yet to decide on this collateral program scrap. "BI was learning the concept. The \b \highlight22\uc2 public\b0 \highlight\uc2  need not worry about it." \par \par \b \highlight22\uc2 Uncertain\b0 \highlight\par \par \uc2  Director general of financial institute at the ministry of finance Darmin Nasution asserted it would be \b \highlight22\uc2 uncertain\b0 \highlight\uc2  that the banking collateral reduction would be implemented on July 31, 2002. \par \par \uc2  "The reduction of collateral would certainly be implemented, but it is not certain to take place on the end of this month because it was being discussed." \par \par \uc2  Darmin argued the government would still guarantee the whole fund of third parties prevailing at banks. "100 percent of third parties fund are still guaranteed. We will only reduce it gradually, starting of bank transaction such as currency swap." \par \par \uc2  The member of House finance and bank commission Rizal Djalil deplored government statement on the reduction of bank collateral fund. "its time schedule was not yet being provided, so what on earth to reduce it. DPR had not known the preparation of government to reduce the gradual collateral." \par \par \uc2  He said the government had not made any technical preparation to perform it. "If there was not preparation, it is better no to give any statement, or else banks and their customers would be restless." (htr/hh). \par \par \uc2 Document bisnis0020020722dy7k0005n\par }\page {\par\fs20{\*\shppict{\pict\pngblip\picw298\pich36\picscaley100\picscalex100\picwgoal4470\pichgoal540
