rt that militant workers did not significantly affect investment or overall business. \par \par \uc2  "Based on research conducted by the International Labor Organization (ILO) and the Organization for \b \highlight22\uc2 Economic\b0 \highlight\uc2  Cooperation and Development (OECD), militant labor action is only a seventh factor in plummeting business," Rekson said separately. \par \par \uc2  He said political stability, a legal guarantee and investment security were the three most dominant factors in \b \highlight22\uc2 economic\b0 \highlight\uc2  development. \par \par \uc2  Dita said that apart from the country's ambiguous \b \highlight22\uc2 economic\b0 \highlight\uc2  regulations, regional autonomy should also be partly blamed as it further supported corrupt practices. \par \par \uc2  Earlier on Sunday, Jacob said militant labor unions had gone too far, leading to a significant drop in domestic and foreign investment in the country. \par \par \uc2  He said their actions had rendered the business climate less attractive for investment, with many businesspeople relocating factories to neighboring Asian countries. \par \par \uc2  Direct foreign investment has plunged drastically in Indonesia. In the first five months of this year, government-approved foreign investment reached only US$1.6 billion, a 60 percent fall from 2001. \par \par \uc2  Copyright 2002 The Jakarta Post. \par \par \uc2 Document jkpost0020020722dy7n000md\par }\page {\par\fs20{\*\shppict{\pict\pngblip\picw298\pich36\picscaley100\picscalex100\picwgoal4470\pichgoal540
