\par\par \b \uc2  KPEN calls MPR to help solve unemployment problem. \b0\par\par\uc2 507 \uc2 words\par \uc2 3 August 2002\par \uc2 Jakarta Post\par \uc2 JKPOST\par  13 \par \uc2 English\par \uc2 (c) 2002 The Jakarta Post\par \par \uc2  A'an Suryana, The Jakarta Post, Jakarta \par \par \uc2  The National \b \highlight22\uc2 Economic\b0 \highlight\uc2  Recovery Committee (KPEN) called on lawmakers to seek ways to help resolve the country's pressing \b \highlight22\uc2 economic\b0 \highlight\uc2  difficulties, particularly unemployment. \par \par \uc2  "Although there are signs that certain (macroeconomic) indicators are improving, there are still many \b \highlight22\uc2 economic\b0 \highlight\uc2  problems that must be addressed," KPEN chairman Sofjan Wanandi told reporters at a media conference. \par \par \uc2  The People's Consultative Assembly (MPR), the country's highest lawmaking body, is holding a 10-day Annual Session to formulate ways to boost the country's fragile democracy. One of the main items on the agenda is the amendment to the Constitution. \par \par \uc2  But Sofjan said that lawmakers should also make solving \b \highlight22\uc2 economic\b0 \highlight\uc2  problems a priority. \par \par \uc2  He told The Jakarta Post that KPEN supported plans by lawmakers to issue a special MPR decree on \b \highlight22\uc2 economic\b0 \highlight\uc2  recovery, but quickly added that the decree must stipulate clear measures and specific targets for the government in fixing the \b \highlight22\uc2 economy\b0 \highlight\uc2 , particularly on how to resolve the unemployment problem. \par \par \uc2  Economists previously criticized the MPR decree draft as being "too general and lacking in clear-cut guidelines". \par \par \uc2  The decree on \b \highlight22\uc2 economic\b0 \highlight\uc2  recovery is meant to provide guidelines for the government to accelerate \b \highlight22\uc2 economic\b0 \highlight\uc2  recovery. \par \par \uc2  Sofjan said that the country's \b \highlight22\uc2 economy\b0 \highlight\uc2 , which contracted by nearly 14 percent in 1998 in the wake of the political and \b \highlight22\uc2 economic\b0 \highlight\uc2  crisis, was still moving at a slow pace and this was not enough to significantly absorb the millions of people put out of work by the crisis. \par \par \uc2  He explained that while the cash-strapped government could not be expected to boost \b \highlight22\uc2 spending\b0 \highlight\uc2  to push \b \highlight22\uc2 economic\b0 \highlight\uc2  growth, other \b \highlight22\uc2 economic\b0 \highlight\uc2  movers, like export and investment, were languishing due to various \b \highlight22\uc2 uncertainties\b0 \highlight\uc2 , such as labor disputes and security problems. \par \par \uc2  "The impact of the slow \b \highlight22\uc2 economic\b0 \highlight\uc2  recovery process has limited job creation and spurred a rise in unemployment," Sofjan said. \par \par \uc2  "Every year, there are 2.5 million new people looking for work. Unfortunately, the current 3 percent \b \highlight22\uc2 economic\b0 \highlight\uc2  growth can only absorb 1.5 million people," he said. \par \par \uc2  According to one estimate, the number of unemployed in this country is about 40 million. This figure will rise with the tens of thousands of workers expelled from Malaysia. \par \par \uc2  "Unemployment is a very serious problem. This could create instability," Sofjan said. \par \par \uc2  He urged the government to create a conducive climate for investors and businesses to help resolve the unemployment problem. \par \par \uc2  He said it was high time that lawmakers create the momentum needed to accelerate an \b \highlight22\uc2 economic\b0 \highlight\uc2  recovery. \par \par \uc2  KPEN also urged the government to immediately launch measures to create legal certainty, curb corruption and boost security to give investors peace of mind. \par \par \uc2  "The investment bill must be deliberated and passed into law immediately," it said. \par \par \uc2  He added that investors concerned about labor rulings that overly protect workers at employers' expense must be quickly addressed to prevent investors from moving out of the country. \par \par \uc2  He added that rampant smuggling, which had created serious problems for local businesses, must also be curbed. \par \par \uc2  Copyright 2002 The Jakarta Post. \par \par \uc2 Document jkpost0020020803dy830000t\par }\page {\par\fs20{\*\shppict{\pict\pngblip\picw298\pich36\picscaley100\picscalex100\picwgoal4470\pichgoal540
