\par\par \b \uc2  Commission agrees on  \highlight22\uc2 economic \highlight\uc2  recovery. \b0\par\par\uc2 514 \uc2 words\par \uc2 5 August 2002\par \uc2 Jakarta Post\par \uc2 JKPOST\par  3 \par \uc2 English\par \uc2 (c) 2002 The Jakarta Post\par \par \uc2  Fitri Wulandari, The Jakarta Post, Jakarta \par \par \uc2  Commission B at the People's Consultative Assembly (MPR) Annual Session agreed on Sunday to a draft \b \highlight22\uc2 economic\b0 \highlight\uc2  recovery decree but failed to give a clear-cut strategy on how to accelerate the \b \highlight22\uc2 economic\b0 \highlight\uc2  recovery process. \par \par \uc2  "The decree is necessary as a political umbrella for \b \highlight22\uc2 economic\b0 \highlight\uc2  recovery as the current process has failed to meet expectations," Chairunnisa of the Golkar Party faction, the second largest party, told the commission hearing on Sunday. \par \par \uc2  MPR's Commission B is tasked with drafting four MPR decrees, including on \b \highlight22\uc2 economic\b0 \highlight\uc2  recovery. \par \par \uc2  Factions cited a lack of coordination among government institutions, legal and security \b \highlight22\uc2 uncertainty\b0 \highlight\uc2 , political instability and rampant corruption as the main factors that had stalled the process. \par \par \uc2  The \b \highlight22\uc2 economic\b0 \highlight\uc2  recovery decree is supposedly aimed at providing the government with guidelines for difficult \b \highlight22\uc2 economic\b0 \highlight\uc2  policies, including privatization, reducing \b \highlight22\uc2 subsidies\b0 \highlight\uc2  and \b \highlight22\uc2 public\b0 \highlight\uc2  debt management to help avoid disputes between government officials and legislators. \par \par \uc2  The draft recommends, among other things, creating legal and security certainty to lure investors, correcting relations with international creditors and managing the state \b \highlight22\uc2 budget\b0 \highlight\uc2  by optimizing \b \highlight22\uc2 tax\b0 \highlight\uc2  revenue. \par \par \uc2  Economists have criticized the draft as "too general and lacking in clear-cut guidelines". \par \par \uc2  Take foreign debt, for example, which amounted to 54 percent of the total foreign and domestic debt of US$135 billion. \par \par \uc2  The draft recommends renegotiation with international creditors for a hair cut, rescheduling and conversion to ease the burden of foreign debt in the state \b \highlight22\uc2 budget\b0 \highlight\uc2 . \par \par \uc2  Economists have also suggested that the government push for a debt for poverty reduction swap and a debt to \b \highlight22\uc2 public\b0 \highlight\uc2  utility swap in order to ease the burden of foreign debt in the state \b \highlight22\uc2 budget\b0 \highlight\uc2  while serving \b \highlight22\uc2 public\b0 \highlight\uc2  interests. \par \par \uc2  On the privatization of state-owned enterprises (SOEs) to tap the \b \highlight22\uc2 budget deficit\b0 \highlight\uc2  and to revive foreign investor confidence, the draft recommends selective privatization. \par \par \uc2  Economists have suggested that privatization of SOEs should be based on increasing efficiency and transparency to eliminate corruption. \par \par \uc2  The government has failed to meet the target of Rp 6.5 trillion (about US$718 million) in privatization proceeds. It has only managed to rake up Rp 2.6 trillion as political opposition, including from the House, to selling state assets to foreigners remains strong, including to the high-profile sale of PT Semen Gresik. \par \par \uc2  In Sunday's session, the legislators urged the government to review its relations, particularly with the International Monetary Fund (IMF), considered to have reduced the country's independency in taking its own \b \highlight22\uc2 economic policy\b0 \highlight\uc2 . \par \par \uc2  "Imbalanced relations with international organizations needs to be corrected, particularly with the IMF," Chairunnisa added. \par \par \uc2  Legislators, however, did not specify what sort of action was needed to reduce dependency on the IMF. \par \par \uc2  MPR recommendations for \b \highlight22\uc2 economic\b0 \highlight\uc2  recovery: (1) Clean central and regional government, (2) Legal certainty to lure investors, (3) Balanced relations with international creditors, (4) Renegotiate foreign debt to get a hair cut and rescheduling (5) Managing the state \b \highlight22\uc2 budget\b0 \highlight\uc2  effectively through optimizing \b \highlight22\uc2 tax\b0 \highlight\uc2  revenue and selective privatization of SOEs, (6) Strengthening commitment to small-and middle-sized enterprises (SMEs). \par \par \uc2  Copyright 2002 The Jakarta Post. \par \par \uc2 Document jkpost0020020805dy8500002\par }\page {\par\fs20{\*\shppict{\pict\pngblip\picw139\pich40\picscaley100\picscalex100\picwgoal2085\pichgoal600
