n on the part of other ministers needed to resolve the various problems faced in manufacturing and trade activities. The country, which is in its fifth consecutive year of an \b \highlight22\uc2 economic\b0 \highlight\uc2  crisis, actually needed such a crisis management center more than four years ago, but the President's top priority seemed to lie somewhere else. It thus would be better and more effective in helping resolve \b \highlight22\uc2 economic\b0 \highlight\uc2  problems if the President or the Cabinet eventually makes a magnanimous decision to upgrade and broaden Rini's crisis center that works with the highest sense of urgency to resolve problems by executive fiat on the spot at least on a monthly basis. * The Jakarta Post. \par \par \uc2 Document antara0020020808dy86000gq\par }\page {\par\fs20{\*\shppict{\pict\pngblip\picw298\pich36\picscaley100\picscalex100\picwgoal4470\pichgoal540
