\par\par \b \uc2  DISAPPOINTING, RI'S FAILURE TO SUPPLY LNG TO CHINA - MP. \b0\par\par\uc2 568 \uc2 words\par \uc2 8 August 2002\par \uc2 LKBN ANTARA\par \uc2 ANTARA\par \uc2 English\par \uc2 (c) 2002 Asia Pulse Pte Limited. Asia Pulse gives no warranty or guarantee as to the accuracy of the information, Asia Pulse shall not be liable for errors or omissions in, or delays or interruptions to or cessation of delivery of, the data through its negligence or otherwise.\par \par \uc2  Jakarta, Aug 8 (ANTARA) - Indonesia's failure in winning a tender for the supply of liquefied natural gas (LNG) to Guangdong province, China, was regrettable because theoretically Indonesia was more qualified than the other bidders, a member of the \b \highlight22\uc2 House of Representatives\b0 \highlight\uc2  said here. The Chinese government on Thursday decided to choose Australia's North West Shelf Venture for the LNG shipments to Guangdong province. "I don't understand this failure because theoretically Indonesia is more competitive than Australia and Qatar," Priyo Budi Santoso from Golkar faction said. He blamed the government's poor lobbying for the failure to win the tender, which is expected to help the government reduce its \b \highlight22\uc2 budget\b0 \highlight\uc2 's \b \highlight22\uc2 deficit\b0 \highlight\uc2 . Priyo said the appointment of Taufik Kiemas, President Megawati Soekarnoputeri's husband, as the leader of the government lobbying team was a poor decision. "It is a big mistake and I assumed the failure was also caused by Taufik Kiemas' involvement," he said. \par \par \uc2   The government should establish an official lobbying team which is led by senior government officials such as the Coordinating Minister for \b \highlight22\uc2 Economic\b0 \highlight\uc2  Affairs or the President herself, he said. After a two-month delay, Beijing finally appointed ALNG, a consortium led by Australian energy giant Woodside Petroleum Ltd that has won a 25-year deal on the initial shipment of LNG to a terminal in south China's Guangdong province, the first of its kind in the country, the Xinhua news agency said. Due to the failure, the government has stopped dreaming about the US$1 billion it could have earned annually from the project. Last March, Indonesian President Megawati Soekarnoputri visited China as part of her East Asian and South Asian trip. During the visit, she told reporters that she was quite optimistic that Indonesia would win the tender. In her meeting with British Prime Minister Tony Blair, Megawati also asked for his moral support to enable Indonesia to win the tender. Indonesia was in the tender represented by British Petroleum (BP) Indonesia, offering its LNG from its field in Tangguh, Papua province, starting in 2005. Beijing however selected Tangguh gas field as the supplier for China's second LNG import terminal, to be constructed in the eastern province of Fujian, Xinhua said. The contract to supply LNG to Fujian is only one-eighth of Guangdong's contract. "It is only a consolation to our disappointment," Priyo commented. Airing a different opinion, a mines and energy industry observer Khurtubi said Australia won the bid because it offered a lower price compared with Indonesia and Qatar. "Australia was able to offer a lower price because it obtained LNG from the existing fields while Tangguh field is classified as a grassroots field," he said. Khurtubi blamed the current law on oil and gas management as the main cause of the poor lobbying performance. "Lobbying is important, but it could also be one of the sources of failure," he said. But the new law on oil and natural gas management is the major cause of the failure, he said. The law has blurred the role between the state-owned oil company and the production sharing contractors in managing the oil and gas business, he said. "Such \b \highlight22\uc2 uncertainty\b0 \highlight\uc2  is clearly spotted by the Chinese government. That is why the law must be amended otherwise foreing investors will remain in doubt about Indonesia," he said. \par \par \uc2 Document antara0020020814dy8800002\par }\page {\par\fs20{\*\shppict{\pict\pngblip\picw298\pich36\picscaley100\picscalex100\picwgoal4470\pichgoal540
