\par\par \b \uc2  TV stations entering era of fiercer competition. \b0\par\par\uc2 533 \uc2 words\par \uc2 8 August 2002\par \uc2 Jakarta Post\par \uc2 JKPOST\par  4 \par \uc2 English\par \uc2 (c) 2002 The Jakarta Post\par \par \uc2  The Jakarta Post, Jakarta \par \par \uc2  Indonesia's mushrooming television stations are entering an era of fiercer competition amid the \b \highlight22\uc2 uncertain\b0 \highlight\uc2  political and \b \highlight22\uc2 economic\b0 \highlight\uc2  situation, a more selective \b \highlight22\uc2 public\b0 \highlight\uc2  and the presence of foreign TV programs in Indonesia, according to TV media observers. \par \par \uc2  Veven S.P. Wardana and Garin Nugroho said the presence of eleven TV stations would affect the electronic media at home but benefit the \b \highlight22\uc2 public\b0 \highlight\uc2 . \par \par \uc2  Both were responding to the grand launch of Lativi TV station here on Wednesday. \par \par \uc2  Garin said that eleven was too many because it would force the TV stations to stage an all-out battle to gain as much income as possible (mostly from advertising and TV program sponsorships) to cover their high production costs and to achieve a break-even point (for new TV stations). \par \par \uc2  "Longer-established TV stations RCTI, SCTV, Indosiar, ANTV, TPI and TVRI have faced financial difficulties in covering their operational costs; now, many more new TV stations are on the air in fiercer competition. The increase in the number of TV stations is not in balance with the growth of advertising," he told The Jakarta Post here on Wednesday. \par \par \uc2  The new TV stations are Trans TV, Metro TV, TV7, Lativi and Global TV. Besides, Garin said, the capital-intensive TV stations must compete with regional TV stations in the provinces, including Bali and Papua, and foreign TV stations such as CNN, MTV and many others in neighboring countries Malaysia, Singapore and Australia. \par \par \uc2  "There will be victims of the fiercer competition in the near future," he said. \par \par \uc2  Veven regretted that almost all TV stations frequently sacrifice the \b \highlight22\uc2 public\b0 \highlight\uc2  interest in favor of competition for advertisements. \par \par \uc2  "But, the longer the TV stations runs their programs, viewers will become more selective and will no longer watch sponsored programs, preferring those that cater for viewers' interests," he said. \par \par \uc2  Both Veven and Garin were of the same opinion that all the TV stations were still searching for their own identity. \par \par \uc2  "The TV stations have almost identical programs. Most entertainment programs, especially films, are imported. It is not a hasty conclusion to make that TV station programs are radio programs plus pictures. They have yet to show their strength or difference from radio stations," he said. \par \par \uc2  They also said that TV stations lacked qualified human resources to manage programs to attract more viewers. \par \par \uc2  Meanwhile, Abdul Latief, owner of Lativi, said he was fighting hard to meet his target of preparing more domestic programs in the coming year. \par \par \uc2  "We are growing to be a national TV station, with 60 percent local program content and 40 percent foreign programs," he said, adding that he had invested Rp 60 billion in the TV industry. \par \par \uc2  He added that he was optimistic that the TV station would reach a break-even point within the next four years. \par \par \uc2  Latief, also a former manpower minister, acknowledged he enjoyed the competition and would survive it. \par \par \uc2  "We are training our human resources to be more qualified in managing programs, especially local ones, and to prepare a more investigative news presentation. Our main mission is to provide educational entertainment and accurate news for the \b \highlight22\uc2 public\b0 \highlight\uc2 ," he said. \par \par \uc2  Copyright 2002 The Jakarta Post. \par \par \uc2 Document jk