\par\par \b \uc2  Bank loans still hard to come by for real sector due to  \highlight22\uc2 uncertainties \highlight\uc2 . \b0\par\par\uc2 811 \uc2 words\par \uc2 12 August 2002\par \uc2 Jakarta Post\par \uc2 JKPOST\par  13 \par \uc2 English\par \uc2 (c) 2002 The Jakarta Post\par \par \uc2  Dadan Wijaksana, The Jakarta Post, Jakarta \par \par \uc2  Hefty cuts in \b \highlight22\uc2 Bank Indonesia\b0 \highlight\uc2 's benchmark interest rate have apparently failed to persuade banks to boost lending to the anemic real sector, in what analysts believe to be the result of a poor investment climate here. \par \par \uc2  Analysts Ryan Kiryanto and Edwin Syahruzad said that the lowering of \b \highlight22\uc2 central bank interest rates\b0 \highlight\uc2  should have spurred lending activity as loans became cheaper, but ultimately it was a good investment climate that would encourage banks to lend more money. \par \par \uc2  "A lower interest rate environment will definitely help, but other stimuli are needed too. In the end, it'll all come down to what the investment climate looks like here," Edwin, of the Danareksa Research Institute, told The Jakarta Post last week. \par \par \uc2  Reviving the real sector by pushing banks to channel more loans is crucial to help push \b \highlight22\uc2 economic\b0 \highlight\uc2  growth and accelerate the country's \b \highlight22\uc2 economic\b0 \highlight\uc2  recovery. \par \par \uc2  For this year, the government has targeted 4 percent \b \highlight22\uc2 economic\b0 \highlight\uc2  growth, although some, including the International Monetary Fund and National Development Planning Board (Bappenas) have recently revised their growth forecasts lower, to 3 percent to 3.5 percent. \par \par \uc2  Ryan said another reason for the slower lending activity was because there was a time lag before bank lending rates could be adjusted to the lower \b \highlight22\uc2 Bank Indonesia\b0 \highlight\uc2  rate. \par \par \uc2  "When \b \highlight22\uc2 Bank Indonesia\b0 \highlight\uc2  lowers its interest rate, a bank needs two or three months before it finally lowers lending rates, as it has to lower its time-deposit rates first," Ryan told the Post. \par \par \uc2  Since January of this year \b \highlight22\uc2 Bank Indonesia\b0 \highlight\uc2  had been cutting its benchmark interest rate in the hope of giving leeway to the banking sector to improve its intermediary role by expanding more loans. Another objective is to help ease the burden on the government in covering the interest repayments on government bonds issued in the late 1990s to bailed-out banks. \par \par \uc2  The relatively loose monetary \b \highlight22\uc2 policy\b0 \highlight\uc2  has been made possible amid lower inflation and a stronger exchange rate of the rupiah against the U.S. dollar. \par \par \uc2  Although \b \highlight22\uc2 Bank Indonesia\b0 \highlight\uc2  data shows that bank loans increased during the first half of this year, they still failed to live up to expectations. \par \par \uc2  New credit approvals throughout the first semester reached around Rp 22.5 trillion of a total Rp 346.9 trillion in outstanding loans. Of new loans, 25 percent were channeled to the trading sector, while the trading services and industrial/manufacturing sectors took 20 percent and 19 percent respectively of the loans. \par \par \uc2  During the same period, the benchmark interest rate on \b \highlight22\uc2 Bank Indonesia\b0 \highlight\uc2  one-month SBI promissory notes dropped from 17.50 percent in early January to 15.06 percent in June. Currently, the rate is hovering at 14.87 percent. \par \par \uc2  In comparison, lending rate is currently set at 19 percent to 22 percent, while time-deposit rate is hovering at 13 percent to 14.5 percent. \par \par \uc2  New loan approvals in the fourth quarter of 2001 stood at Rp 20 trillion, when the \b \highlight22\uc2 central bank\b0 \highlight\uc2 's \b \highlight22\uc2 interest rates\b0 \highlight\uc2  were still hovering at around 18 percent. \par \par \uc2  According to Ryan and Edwin, such a small amount of new loans should explain why in the first semester there was a huge drop in domestic investment approvals, declining by almost 70 percent compared with the same period last year. \par \par \uc2  Data from the Investment Coordinating Board (BKPM) shows that domestic investment approvals for the first six months of the year reached only about Rp 11 trillion, compared with nearly Rp 40 trillion posted last year in the same period. \par \par \uc2  Legal \b \highlight22\uc2 uncertainties\b0 \highlight\uc2 , among other things, are widely regarded to have scared investors away from the country. The domestic political situation, labor conflicts and development in the global \b \highlight22\uc2 economy\b0 \highlight\uc2  also played a part in damaging the investment climate. \par \par \uc2  President Megawati Soekarnoputri even admitted in her speech before lawmakers last week that the country's legal reforms had been slow, thus creating \b \highlight22\uc2 uncertainty\b0 \highlight\uc2  among investors, both foreign and domestic. \par \par \uc2  The relatively risky investment climate here has caused banks, badly hit by the 1997 financial crisis, to be extra careful in channeling their money, thus resulting in the slow growth of lending. \par \par \uc2  Also contributing to the banking sector's reluctance to provide more lending was its dependence on the lucrative revenues from recapitalization (recap) bonds, which currently dominate banks' productive assets. \par \par \uc2  Loans made up only 34.7 percent of the banking industry's productive assets, with 44 percent consisting of recap bonds. \par \par \uc2  So far, of the total interest revenue enjoyed by the banking industry, almost 45 percent has come from the interest on recap bonds. \par \par \uc2  Analysts also said that the slow lending activity in the first half should put \b \highlight22\uc2 Bank Indonesia\b0 \highlight\uc2 's target, set earlier this year, for bank loans to grow by Rp 62.12 trillion this year, at risk. \par \par \uc2  Copyright 2002 The Jakarta Post. \par \par \uc2 Document jkpost0020020812dy8c00009\par }\page {\par\fs20{\*\shppict{\pict\pngblip\picw139\pich40\picscaley100\picscalex100\picwgoal2085\pichgoal600
