\par\par \b \uc2  Doubts cloud potency of  \highlight22\uc2 economic \highlight\uc2  recovery decree. \b0\par\par\uc2 552 \uc2 words\par \uc2 13 August 2002\par \uc2 Jakarta Post\par \uc2 JKPOST\par  13 \par \uc2 English\par \uc2 (c) 2002 The Jakarta Post\par \par \uc2  Dadan Wijaksana and A'an Suryana, The Jakarta Post, Jakarta \par \par \uc2  Economists voiced their doubt that the People's Consultative Assembly (MPR) decree on \b \highlight22\uc2 economic\b0 \highlight\uc2  recovery could accelerate a recovery process because it did not provide more power to the government to execute key \b \highlight22\uc2 economic\b0 \highlight\uc2  policies. \par \par \uc2  Raden Pardede of the Danareksa Research Institute said on Monday that the government was often locked in endless debates with legislators when talking about critical \b \highlight22\uc2 economic\b0 \highlight\uc2  measures to help push for a faster \b \highlight22\uc2 economic\b0 \highlight\uc2  recovery. \par \par \uc2  "We cannot expect the government to push for higher growth, while at the same time the House often gives the government a hard time whenever it executes policies," he told The Jakarta Post. \par \par \uc2  The decree on \b \highlight22\uc2 economic\b0 \highlight\uc2  recovery, issued by the MPR during its Annual Session, ending on Sunday, is meant to provide general guidelines for the government to speed up the country's \b \highlight22\uc2 economic\b0 \highlight\uc2  recovery process. \par \par \uc2  On many occasions, the government's privatization and asset sale programs have met with delays due to strong rejection from lawmakers. \par \par \uc2  As a consequence, the government has only managed to raise some Rp 2.26 trillion of the Rp 6.5 trillion (US$715 million) of privatization proceeds targeted for this year. \par \par \uc2  Raden said that without the support of the legislature and other state institutions, such as the judicature, it would be impossible for the government as an executive to speed up the recovery process. \par \par \uc2  He said that the role of the judicature was also crucial, particularly in boosting legal certainty. \par \par \uc2  Serious legal \b \highlight22\uc2 uncertainty\b0 \highlight\uc2  has been one of the factors discouraging foreign investors from returning to the country. \par \par \uc2  The need for a special Assembly decree on \b \highlight22\uc2 economic\b0 \highlight\uc2  recovery has often come up as progress has been slow in lifting the country out of its \b \highlight22\uc2 economic\b0 \highlight\uc2  slump, which resulted from the late 1990s devastating \b \highlight22\uc2 economic\b0 \highlight\uc2  crisis. \par \par \uc2  The country's \b \highlight22\uc2 economy\b0 \highlight\uc2 , which contracted by nearly 14 percent in 1998, is moving at a slow pace and failing to keep up with the need for sufficient job creation to absorb the millions of people put out of work by the crisis. \par \par \uc2  Apparent setbacks in several \b \highlight22\uc2 economic\b0 \highlight\uc2  indicators, such as exports and investments, have only added to the pressure for efforts to push the recovery process. \par \par \uc2  The National Development Planning Agency (Bappenas) has painted an even bleaker outlook, projecting the country's \b \highlight22\uc2 economy\b0 \highlight\uc2  to grow this year by only about 3 percent, which is below the state \b \highlight22\uc2 budget\b0 \highlight\uc2 's target of 4 percent. \par \par \uc2  The modest growth would only absorb 1.5 million workers, which is way below the estimate of 2.5 million new jobseekers this year. \par \par \uc2  Meanwhile, economist Pande Radja Silalahi also said that the decree would not be effective as it merely provided recommendations and lacked specific measures. \par \par \uc2  Pande lashed out at broad statements made by the Assembly in the decree, saying that the MPR should detail the items. \par \par \uc2  "We know that investments are crucial to propel \b \highlight22\uc2 economic\b0 \highlight\uc2  growth, however, the Assembly has failed in the decree to stipulate measures on how to increase investments," he said. \par \par \uc2  The Assembly should show the government how to raise investments, such as what the government should do to assure domestic security and legal certainty. \par \par \uc2  The MPR decree on \b \highlight22\uc2 economic\b0 \highlight\uc2  recovery stipulates five \b \highlight22\uc2 policy\b0 \highlight\uc2  principles and 10 \b \highlight22\uc2 policy\b0 \highlight\uc2  recommendations. \par \par \uc2  Copyright 2002 The Jakarta Post. \par \par \uc2 Document jkpost0020020812dy8d000h9\par }\page {\par\fs20{\*\shppict{\pict\pngblip\picw298\pich36\picscaley100\picscalex100\picwgoal4470\pichgoal540
