\par\par \b \uc2  Market awaits concrete action from govt after MPR session. \b0\par\par\uc2 479 \uc2 words\par \uc2 15 August 2002\par \uc2 Jakarta Post\par \uc2 JKPOST\par  2 \par \uc2 English\par \uc2 (c) 2002 The Jakarta Post\par \par \uc2  A'an Suryana, The Jakarta Post, Jakarta \par \par \uc2  While the government may be let down with the lukewarm response of the financial market to the positive outcome of last week's People's Consultative Assembly (MPR) annual session, analysts said that foreign investors would continue to adopt a wait and see attitude until there was more concrete evidence that the government could resolve the various \b \highlight22\uc2 uncertainties\b0 \highlight\uc2  plaguing the country. \par \par \uc2  "The market's response is actually positive, but they need to see more evidence," Citibank economist Anton Gunawan told The Jakarta Post on Wednesday. \par \par \uc2  Last week, the MPR, Indonesia's highest \b \highlight22\uc2 legislative\b0 \highlight\uc2  body, approved several constitutional reforms which experts say will put Indonesia on the right track towards democracy and help end the unstable political and \b \highlight22\uc2 economic\b0 \highlight\uc2  situation which has gripped the country since the late 1990s following the downfall of former authoritarian president Soeharto, and the regional \b \highlight22\uc2 economic\b0 \highlight\uc2  crisis. \par \par \uc2  The positive results of the MPR session, among others a direct presidential election and the elimination of military parliamentary seats to boost civilian control, has been applauded by the international press, with editorials saying that Jakarta is heading in the right direction. \par \par \uc2  But the positive international press coverage has not boosted foreign investors sentiment in the country as reflected in the rupiah and the local stock market. \par \par \uc2  This seems to disappoint the government. \par \par \uc2  "The market should have given a much warmer response," said Mahendra Siregar, a staff member at the Office of the Coordinating Minister for the \b \highlight22\uc2 Economy\b0 \highlight\uc2 . \par \par \uc2  The rupiah only increased slightly to around the Rp 9,000 level during the past couple of days following the MPR session, which ended on Sunday. The Jakarta Stock Exchange composite index had also been hovering at around the 448 level. \par \par \uc2  Anton said although investors were heartened with the violence-free and peaceful MPR annual session, investors still wanted to see if the government could deliver pro-market \b \highlight22\uc2 economic\b0 \highlight\uc2  policies. \par \par \uc2  He said that investors were now waiting for the 2003 state \b \highlight22\uc2 budget\b0 \highlight\uc2  draft, which is expected to be delivered by President Megawati Soekarnoputri on Friday. \par \par \uc2  "The government should exercise prudent macroeconomic \b \highlight22\uc2 policy\b0 \highlight\uc2  in the state \b \highlight22\uc2 budget\b0 \highlight\uc2 ." \par \par \uc2  The government may be tempted to adopt popular \b \highlight22\uc2 policy\b0 \highlight\uc2  which could further strain the state \b \highlight22\uc2 budget\b0 \highlight\uc2  in hopes of winning the 2004 general election, some analysts have said. \par \par \uc2  Center for Information and Development Studies (CIDES) economist Umar Juoro concurred, saying that to benefit from the positive outcome of the MPR session, the government must continue measures to revive foreign investors confidence including by creating legal certainty, and resolving the widespread labor conflicts. \par \par \uc2  "The government must continue measures to attract foreign investors by pushing legal certainty and security assurance," he said. \par \par \uc2  He said that foreign direct investment was crucial to help push \b \highlight22\uc2 economic\b0 \highlight\uc2  growth, which so far was mainly being driven by consumer \b \highlight22\uc2 spending\b0 \highlight\uc2 . \par \par \uc2  Copyright 2002 The Jakarta Post. \par \par \uc2 Document jkpost0020020814dy8f0005s\par }\page {\par\fs20{\*\shppict{\pict\pngblip\picw298\pich36\picscaley100\picscalex100\picwgoal4470\pichgoal540
