\par\par \b  \highlight22\uc2 Economy \highlight\uc2  only grows by 0.52% amid weak exports, investment. \b0\par\par\uc2 700 \uc2 words\par \uc2 16 August 2002\par \uc2 Jakarta Post\par \uc2 JKPOST\par  15 \par \uc2 English\par \uc2 (c) 2002 The Jakarta Post\par \par \uc2  Dadan Wijaksana, The Jakarta Post, Jakarta \par \par \uc2  The \b \highlight22\uc2 economy\b0 \highlight\uc2 , as measured by gross domestic product (GDP), grew by only 0.52 percent in the second quarter of this year due to a slowdown in exports and lower investment, the Central Bureau of Statistics (BPS) said on Thursday. \par \par \uc2  BPS said in a statement that second-quarter \b \highlight22\uc2 economic\b0 \highlight\uc2  growth was mainly attributable to higher consumer and government \b \highlight22\uc2 spending\b0 \highlight\uc2 . \par \par \uc2  It pointed out that consumer \b \highlight22\uc2 spending\b0 \highlight\uc2  grew at a higher rate of 1.16 percent in the second quarter, compared with 0.51 percent in the first, while government \b \highlight22\uc2 spending\b0 \highlight\uc2  was higher, at 2.88 percent from minus 2.35 percent. \par \par \uc2  During the past year, consumer and government \b \highlight22\uc2 spending\b0 \highlight\uc2  were the main source of growth in the \b \highlight22\uc2 economy\b0 \highlight\uc2  as exports and investment remained in the doldrums due to various \b \highlight22\uc2 uncertainties\b0 \highlight\uc2  both at home and overseas. \par \par \uc2  BPS said that while imports grew at a higher rate of 4.28 percent in the second quarter, exports were slower, at a pace of 2.09 percent. Investment also slowed down, at 1.34 percent. \par \par \uc2  "The (GDP) growth has been driven by all sectors of the \b \highlight22\uc2 economy\b0 \highlight\uc2  except mining," BPS said. \par \par \uc2  The weak second-quarter \b \highlight22\uc2 economic\b0 \highlight\uc2  growth is casting doubt on whether the government's 4 percent \b \highlight22\uc2 economic\b0 \highlight\uc2  growth for this year can be achieved. The National Development Planning Board (Bappenas) and other independent experts have previously said that this year's growth would only be around 3 percent. \par \par \uc2  A slower \b \highlight22\uc2 economic\b0 \highlight\uc2  growth would have serious consequences, including a greater number of unemployed people, which, in turn, could create various social problems. \par \par \uc2  But BPS said that second-quarter \b \highlight22\uc2 economic\b0 \highlight\uc2  growth was much better when compared with the same period last year. Year-on-year growth for the quarter was 3.51 percent, which was also mainly driven by stronger domestic \b \highlight22\uc2 spending\b0 \highlight\uc2 . \par \par \uc2  During the first semester of this year, the \b \highlight22\uc2 economy\b0 \highlight\uc2  grew by 2.87 percent over the same period last year. \par \par \uc2  Economists, however, said that if exports and investment remained weak during the next quarters, the year-on-year growth would slow down. That is because the government's ability to spend money would become very limited as it would instead focus on how to limit \b \highlight22\uc2 spending\b0 \highlight\uc2  to ensure that the state \b \highlight22\uc2 budget deficit\b0 \highlight\uc2  was maintained at a safe level of 2.5 percent of GDP. \par \par \uc2  Bank Mandiri economist Martin Panggabean told The Jakarta Post that exports should now become a priority for the government in boosting growth as weakened purchasing power was likely to hurt the current \b \highlight22\uc2 spending\b0 \highlight\uc2  spree. \par \par \uc2  "We can no longer rely on strong domestic consumption alone to boost growth. And as hope for (new) investment is out of the question, I think exports should be a priority," Martin said. \par \par \uc2  To do that, according to Martin, the government should pay more attention to high-end manufacturing and electronic products. \par \par \uc2  "There is still plenty of room for improvement in electronics, and maybe pulp and paper. We should pursue these as alternatives instead of focusing merely on textile and shoe products, which I consider to be sunset industries." \par \par \uc2  Continuing labor conflict and security problems, coupled with the \b \highlight22\uc2 economic\b0 \highlight\uc2  slowdown in the U.S. and Japan, Indonesia's major trading partners, are hurting Indonesia's export products. \par \par \uc2  The above \b \highlight22\uc2 uncertainties\b0 \highlight\uc2  are also discouraging both foreign and domestic investors from making new investments in the country. \par \par \uc2  Nevertheless, despite all the gloomy outlook, Martin was optimistic that the country remained on track to achieve a growth target of 4 percent. \par \par \uc2  "With the (year-on-year GDP growth) figure, which is higher than I expected, the government should be on track for achieving the full-year target of 4 percent," he said. \par \par \uc2  Sharing Martin's view, BPS head Sudarti Surbakti said the country's growth target was attainable "if conditions remain good." \par \par \uc2  Eye-box \par \par \uc2  Growth of GDP components in Q2 (%) \par \par \uc2  - \par \par \uc2  quarter-on-quarter year-on-year -1. Household \b \highlight22\uc2 spending\b0 \highlight\uc2  1.16 6.30 2. Govt \b \highlight22\uc2 spending\b0 \highlight\uc2  2.88 9.40 3. Fixed capital formation 1.34 -1.01 4. Exports 2.09 -7.09 5. Imports 4.28 -21.6 - GDP 0.52 3.51 - Source: BPS \par \par \uc2  Copyright 2002 The Jakarta Post. \par \par \uc2 Document jkpost0020020815dy8g000bj\par }\page {\par\fs20{\*\shppict{\pict\pngblip\picw139\pich40\picscaley100\picscalex100\picwgoal2085\pichgoal600
