\par\par \b \uc2  AUSTRIAN INVESTORS WANT LAW ENFORCEMENT IN RI GUARANTEED. \b0\par\par\uc2 490 \uc2 words\par \uc2 17 August 2002\par \uc2 LKBN ANTARA\par \uc2 ANTARA\par \uc2 English\par \uc2 (c) 2002 Asia Pulse Pte Limited. Asia Pulse gives no warranty or guarantee as to the accuracy of the information, Asia Pulse shall not be liable for errors or omissions in, or delays or interruptions to or cessation of delivery of, the data through its negligence or otherwise.\par \par \uc2  Brussels, Aug 17 (ANTARA) - A number of Austrian businessmen have expressed interest in investing more capital in Indonesia but would like to see law enforcement and legal consistency in the country guaranteed. So far, 32 Austrian companies have been operating in Indonesia for a relatively long time. According to Indonesian Ambassador to Austria, TA Samodra Sriwijaja, Austrian capital owners have adopted a wait-and-see stance until law enforcement conditions in Indonesia are conducive for capital investment. In a statement to ANTARA here Saturday, Ambassador Samodra Sriwidjaja said he had explained to would-be Austrian investors that Indonesia was launching reform drives in various fields, including in law enforcement. The ambassador pointed to the recent constitutional amendments during the 2002 annual session of the People's Consultative Assembly (MPR) which, he said, would drastically improve the Indonesian legal system. \par \par \uc2   He also said that beside legal reform, Indonesia would also deregulate various laws governing business activities and capital investment. He said that the Indonesian government through the Indonesian Embassy in Vienna had been actively engaged in negotiations for a bilateral agreement dealing with investment promotion and guarantees between Indonesia and Austria. "If the bilateral agreement is reached, Austrian capital investors opening business in Indonesia will be well guaranteed", he said. The Indonesian and Austrian delegations had achieved significant progress in their negoitiations, he said. However, he said the two countries were now waiting for the enactment of the Indonesian investment law which was still being debated by the \b \highlight22\uc2 House\b0 \highlight\b \highlight22\uc2 of Representatives\b0 \highlight\uc2  (DPR). \par \par \uc2  Austrian Companies in Indonesia \par \par \uc2  Meanwhile, data compiled by the Austrian Federal \b \highlight22\uc2 Economic\b0 \highlight\uc2  Chamber reveal that there are at present 32 Austrian companies operating in Indonesia. The Austrian companies engaged in the production of chemical and pharmaceutical goods, along with construction steel and furniture, are operating at a total capital investment of US$ 58 million. Among the Austrian companies are Biochemie at Citeureup, West Java, which produces penicilin and amoxiline and the South Pacific Viscose in Purwakarta, West Java, which produces viscose fibres. Meanwhile, Head of the Embassy's \b \highlight22\uc2 Economic\b0 \highlight\uc2  Affairs, Budi Bowoleksono, said that significant approaches had been made by the Indonesian Embassy not only toward prospective investors but also toward Austrian businessmen who had already invested capital in Indonesia. The Austrian investors in Indonesia have been asked not to relocate their business ventures from Indonesia under the pretext of legal \b \highlight22\uc2 uncertainty\b0 \highlight\uc2 , Bowolaksono said. So far, there has not yet been any single Austrian company trying to relocate their investment from Indonesia to other countries, he said. However, Bowoleksono said that based on data available with the Embassy, Austrian businessmen were beginning to show interest in investing their capital in some relatively nearby countries as those of Central Europe and Eastern Europe, and not in such distant countries as Indonesia. The reasons are purely based on the \b \highlight22\uc2 economic\b0 \highlight\uc2  logic such as the relative proximity and the lower production costs, Bowoleksono said. \par \par \uc2 Document antara0020020820dy8h000bv\par }\page {\par\fs20{\*\shppict{\pict\pngblip\picw298\pich36\picscaley100\picscalex100\picwgoal4470\pichgoal540
