\par\par \b \uc2  New  \highlight22\uc2 tax \highlight\uc2  target,  \highlight22\uc2 subsidy \highlight\uc2  cut will hurt businesses. \b0\par\par\uc2 603 \uc2 words\par \uc2 20 August 2002\par \uc2 Jakarta Post\par \uc2 JKPOST\par  1 \par \uc2 English\par \uc2 (c) 2002 The Jakarta Post\par \par \uc2  A'an Suryana, The Jakarta Post, Jakarta \par \par \uc2  The government's plan to increase \b \highlight22\uc2 tax\b0 \highlight\uc2  revenue and cut \b \highlight22\uc2 subsidies\b0 \highlight\uc2  on fuel and electricity next year will increase the burden on a business sector already struggling to survive from years of downturn, businessmen said on Monday. \par \par \uc2  The chairman of the National \b \highlight22\uc2 Economic\b0 \highlight\uc2  Recovery Committee, Sofjan Wanandi, and the director of the Indonesian Textile Association, Lili Asdjudiredja, both urged the government to revise their plans. \par \par \uc2  "The \b \highlight22\uc2 tax\b0 \highlight\uc2  revenue hike will discourage businessmen from making new investments here," Sofjan said. \par \par \uc2  The two were commenting on the 2003 state \b \highlight22\uc2 budget\b0 \highlight\uc2  draft unveiled by President Megawati Soekarnoputri last week. In the draft, the government proposes an 18.7 percent hike in \b \highlight22\uc2 tax\b0 \highlight\uc2  revenue to Rp 260.8 trillion, to help finance a state \b \highlight22\uc2 budget\b0 \highlight\uc2  heavily burdened by \b \highlight22\uc2 public\b0 \highlight\uc2  debt. \par \par \uc2  The government is also proposing a 39 percent cut in \b \highlight22\uc2 subsidies\b0 \highlight\uc2  to Rp 25.3 trillion, compared to the Rp 41.6 trillion allocated in the 2002 state \b \highlight22\uc2 budget\b0 \highlight\uc2 . \par \par \uc2  The lower \b \highlight22\uc2 subsidies\b0 \highlight\uc2  will translate into higher fuel prices and electricity rates. \par \par \uc2  Megawati said that with the lower \b \highlight22\uc2 subsidies\b0 \highlight\uc2 , the government would have to raise electricity rates by an average of 6 percent every quarter next year. \par \par \uc2  The cut in expensive \b \highlight22\uc2 subsidies\b0 \highlight\uc2  is crucial to help bring down the state \b \highlight22\uc2 budget deficit\b0 \highlight\uc2  to 1.3 percent of gross domestic product from an estimated 2.5 percent in 2002, as part of a \b \highlight22\uc2 policy\b0 \highlight\uc2  aimed at achieving \b \highlight22\uc2 fiscal\b0 \highlight\uc2  sustainability. \par \par \uc2  The state \b \highlight22\uc2 budget\b0 \highlight\uc2  draft is still to be debated by legislators. \par \par \uc2  "These belt-tightening measures will hurt business in general," said Lili. \par \par \uc2  The textile association said earlier many of its members were forced out of business following the drastic cut in energy \b \highlight22\uc2 subsidies\b0 \highlight\uc2  earlier this year, coupled with various \b \highlight22\uc2 uncertainties\b0 \highlight\uc2  including labor conflicts, security problems and falling export orders. \par \par \uc2  There is concern among the business community here that to meet the higher \b \highlight22\uc2 tax\b0 \highlight\uc2  revenue target, the \b \highlight22\uc2 tax\b0 \highlight\uc2  office will squeeze existing corporate \b \highlight22\uc2 tax\b0 \highlight\uc2  payers. \par \par \uc2  Lili warned that forcing companies to pay more \b \highlight22\uc2 taxes\b0 \highlight\uc2  would move them to shift their investment to neighboring countries with more favorable \b \highlight22\uc2 tax\b0 \highlight\uc2  regimes, such as Malaysia, Thailand and Vietnam. \par \par \uc2  He said that these countries had cut corporate \b \highlight22\uc2 taxes\b0 \highlight\uc2  to attract foreign investment. \par \par \uc2  He added that investors in the manufacturing sector would rather shut down their operations and deposit their money in banks, or shrink their operations to cut costs if they were squeezed for more \b \highlight22\uc2 taxes\b0 \highlight\uc2 . \par \par \uc2  "There could be mass layoffs," he warned. \par \par \uc2  Unemployment is one of the country's most pressing problems, with a record high of more than 40 million out of work. \par \par \uc2  "The government must revise the new \b \highlight22\uc2 tax\b0 \highlight\uc2  revenue target. It must focus on curbing corruption," Lili said. \par \par \uc2  Sofjan said that without new investments, it would be impossible for the government to meet the 5 percent \b \highlight22\uc2 economic\b0 \highlight\uc2  growth target in the 2003 state \b \highlight22\uc2 budget\b0 \highlight\uc2  draft. \par \par \uc2  Meanwhile, economist Muhammad Chatib Basri said the higher \b \highlight22\uc2 tax\b0 \highlight\uc2  revenue target would not necessarily be harmful to the business sector, because the country's \b \highlight22\uc2 tax\b0 \highlight\uc2  ratio was still relatively low compared to other countries in the region. \par \par \uc2  He said the 2003 \b \highlight22\uc2 tax\b0 \highlight\uc2  revenue target would merely raise the country's \b \highlight22\uc2 tax\b0 \highlight\uc2  ratio to 13.3 percent from the 13 percent in the current 2002 state \b \highlight22\uc2 budget\b0 \highlight\uc2 . \par \par \uc2  Chatib Basri added that the \b \highlight22\uc2 tax\b0 \highlight\uc2  target would not frighten away foreign investors, because \b \highlight22\uc2 taxes\b0 \highlight\uc2  were not singled out as a main factor in making investments. \par \par \uc2  "Foreign investors are mainly concerned with \b \highlight22\uc2 uncertainties\b0 \highlight\uc2  rather than the \b \highlight22\uc2 tax\b0 \highlight\uc2  issue," he said, pointing to legal \b \highlight22\uc2 uncertainties\b0 \highlight\uc2 , security problems, corruption and labor conflicts. \par \par \uc2  Copyright 2002 The Jakarta Post. \par \par \uc2 Document jkpost0020020819dy8k000mu\par }\page {\par\fs20{\*\shppict{\pict\pngblip\picw298\pich36\picscaley100\picscalex100