\par\par \b \uc2  An austere  \highlight22\uc2 budget \highlight\uc2 . \b0\par\par\uc2 847 \uc2 words\par \uc2 20 August 2002\par \uc2 Jakarta Post\par \uc2 JKPOST\par  6 \par \uc2 English\par \uc2 (c) 2002 The Jakarta Post\par \par \uc2  The state \b \highlight22\uc2 budget\b0 \highlight\uc2  proposal for the \b \highlight22\uc2 fiscal\b0 \highlight\uc2  year 2003 will certainly be contractive on the \b \highlight22\uc2 economy\b0 \highlight\uc2  because total \b \highlight22\uc2 spending\b0 \highlight\uc2  in real terms will decrease by 6 percent and almost 20 percent of the already meager \b \highlight22\uc2 spending\b0 \highlight\uc2  plan will go to servicing foreign debts and to price \b \highlight22\uc2 subsidies\b0 \highlight\uc2  that will not create domestic market demand. \par \par \uc2  More direct and indirect \b \highlight22\uc2 taxes\b0 \highlight\uc2  also will sap consumers' purchasing power, thereby reducing the capacity of private consumer \b \highlight22\uc2 spending\b0 \highlight\uc2  as one of the two main locomotives of growth, besides exports. \par \par \uc2  The \b \highlight22\uc2 spending\b0 \highlight\uc2  plan, like the current \b \highlight22\uc2 budget\b0 \highlight\uc2 , still very much reflects the brunt of the \b \highlight22\uc2 economic\b0 \highlight\uc2  crisis, with government investment (development \b \highlight22\uc2 spending\b0 \highlight\uc2 ) down 5 percent in real terms and routine \b \highlight22\uc2 spending\b0 \highlight\uc2  contracting by almost 12 percent whereas appropriations for regional administrations will increase 6 percent. \par \par \uc2  The \b \highlight22\uc2 budget\b0 \highlight\uc2  proposal will, however, make the market comfortable as it will emphasize \b \highlight22\uc2 fiscal\b0 \highlight\uc2  consolidation by cutting the \b \highlight22\uc2 budget deficit\b0 \highlight\uc2  down to 1.3 percent of gross domestic product (GDP) from 2.5 percent this year and by prioritizing \b \highlight22\uc2 spending\b0 \highlight\uc2  on poverty alleviation and other \b \highlight22\uc2 public\b0 \highlight\uc2  welfare programs such as health and education. \par \par \uc2  The assumptions for the factors that are most influential to \b \highlight22\uc2 budget\b0 \highlight\uc2  estimates seem conservative, estimating GDP growth at 5 percent, inflation at 8 percent, the rupiah exchange rate at Rp 8,700 to the dollar, benchmark interest rate at 13 percent and international crude oil prices at US$20.5 per barrel. \par \par \uc2  The assumptions seem realistic, given the \b \highlight22\uc2 uncertainty\b0 \highlight\uc2  about the world \b \highlight22\uc2 economy\b0 \highlight\uc2 . It is indeed much better to err on the conservative side, rather than being too optimistic and then having to make painful adjustments. \par \par \uc2  The taxpayers should, however, further tighten their belt because electricity and toll roads will for the first time be subject to the 10 percent value-added \b \highlight22\uc2 tax\b0 \highlight\uc2  beginning in January and property \b \highlight22\uc2 tax\b0 \highlight\uc2  will increase as a result of the upcoming rise in the rate of taxable property value. \par \par \uc2  These heavier \b \highlight22\uc2 tax\b0 \highlight\uc2  burdens will come on top of the 6 percent quarterly increase in electricity rates - up by a total of 24 percent for next year. Smokers, who still account for quite a large portion of the population and who usually contribute 5 to 6 percent of total \b \highlight22\uc2 tax\b0 \highlight\uc2  receipts, will also be further squeezed as the government will set tobacco duty by specific amounts, instead of on an ad valorem basis as it is now. \par \par \uc2  The biggest worry, though, is the 26.4 percent rise envisaged in income \b \highlight22\uc2 tax\b0 \highlight\uc2  receipts. Though GDP will most likely expand to 5 percent from an estimated 4 percent this year, and the government argues that much of the increase will be generated by expanding the \b \highlight22\uc2 tax\b0 \highlight\uc2  base, the business community and middle and top income earners will likely remain apprehensive. \par \par \uc2  Experiences so far have shown that every time the government intends to raise more \b \highlight22\uc2 tax\b0 \highlight\uc2  revenues, it is the taxpayers already registered that are hit the hardest due to the inefficient and corrupt \b \highlight22\uc2 tax\b0 \highlight\uc2  administrative system. Taxpayers have accused \b \highlight22\uc2 tax\b0 \highlight\uc2  officials of taking the easy way out. \par \par \uc2  The 105 percent increase in revenue from privatization to as high as Rp 8 trillion is also highly doubtful, given the utterly poor performance in this program since 2000. The government had announced an annual list of dozens of state companies to be sold but very few of them have so far been privatized due to inadequate preparations, or resistance from managements and trade unions or opposition from inordinate nationalist elements in the \b \highlight22\uc2 House of Representatives\b0 \highlight\uc2 . \par \par \uc2  The \b \highlight22\uc2 spending\b0 \highlight\uc2  side of the \b \highlight22\uc2 budget\b0 \highlight\uc2  shows some encouraging progress in \b \highlight22\uc2 fiscal\b0 \highlight\uc2  management. The government will slash \b \highlight22\uc2 spending\b0 \highlight\uc2  on \b \highlight22\uc2 subsidies\b0 \highlight\uc2  by almost 39 percent and on debt servicing by almost 10 percent. \par \par \uc2  Domestic debt (bond) servicing will decline due to the early retirement of a sizable sum of government bonds and the decrease in the benchmark interest rate to 13 percent from an estimated 16 percent throughout this year. \par \par \uc2  Foreign debt service payments will decrease by Rp 32.3 trillion or almost 10 percent of the total \b \highlight22\uc2 spending\b0 \highlight\uc2  plan thanks to the debt rescheduling agreement with the Paris Club of sovereign creditors. \par \par \uc2  It is worth reminding those who like to gain popularity by bashing the International Monetary Fund and blaming it for what they consider the mishandling of the \b \highlight22\uc2 economic\b0 \highlight\uc2  crisis that the debt rescheduling was made possible only under the IMF extended facility to Indonesia. \par \par \uc2  As government investment will decrease by 5 percent in real terms, and consumer \b \highlight22\uc2 spending\b0 \highlight\uc2  will likely weaken next year due to the heavier \b \highlight22\uc2 tax\b0 \highlight\uc2  burdens and higher prices of \b \highlight22\uc2 public\b0 \highlight\uc2  utilities and services, \b \highlight22\uc2 economic\b0 \highlight\uc2  growth will rely mainly on export and domestic investment. Private capital accounts are predicted to suffer another net outflow of $4.2 billion. \par \par \uc2  But exports and domestic investment will never be able to play a bigger role without accelerating corporate debt restructuring to unleash the thousands of businesses from the hostage of their bad debts and by speeding up the sale of distressed assets and of state companies to allow new investors to transform these enterprises into sound, fast growing businesses. \par \par \uc2  Copyright 2002 The Jakarta Post. \par \par \uc2 Document jkpost0020020820dy8k00009\par }\page {\par\fs20{\*\shppict{\pict\pngblip\picw298\pich36\picscaley100\picscalex100\picwgoal4470\pichgoal540
