le, South Korean investors have lodged complaints about the \b \highlight22\uc2 uncertain policy\b0 \highlight\uc2  on employment, irrational salary hike, workers' poor performances, and labor strikes. Some Japanese companies have thus begun relocating their businesses to other states. About 36 South Korean firms have relocated their businesses from Indonesia to Myanmar, Vietnam and other countries, causing 32,000 Indonesian workers to lose their jobs. The exodus of Japanese and South Korean investors from Indonesia reflects the worsening \b \highlight22\uc2 economic\b0 \highlight\uc2  condition in the country. This can bring about a domino effect, causing the exodus of other foreign investors. - ANTARA. \par \par \uc2 Document antara0020020830dy8s00065\par }\page {\par\fs20{\*\shppict{\pict\pngblip\picw298\pich36\picscaley100\picscalex100\picwgoal4470\pichgoal540
