nalized by their respective governments, although investigation into the cases were not completed. \par \par \uc2  According to the Central Bureau of Statistics, exports declined by 6.7 percent to US$27.37 billion during the first half of this year compared to $29.35 billion in the same period last year. \par \par \uc2  Analysts have said that the weak export performance is due to various reasons including business \b \highlight22\uc2 uncertainty\b0 \highlight\uc2  at home and the global \b \highlight22\uc2 economic\b0 \highlight\uc2  slowdown. \par \par \uc2  Improvement in export performance is important to push \b \highlight22\uc2 economic\b0 \highlight\uc2  growth, which so far has been mainly relying on domestic consumption. \par \par \uc2  Rifana said that her office would try to quickly settle the dumping allegations so that foreign buyers would resume buying Indonesian products. \par \par \uc2  Meanwhile, Bachrul Chairi, director of trade protection at the ministry said that Indonesia had also launched antidumping allegations against several imported products to help protect local industries. \par \par \uc2  He pointed out that the ministry was handling some 23 dumping cases against imported products, \par \par \uc2  "We have imposed antidumping charges against seven imported products," he said, but did not give details. \par \par \uc2  Copyright 2002 The Jakarta Post. \par \par \uc2 Document jkpost0020020905dy950000g\par }\page {\par\fs20{\*\shppict{\pict\pngblip\picw298\pich36\picscaley100\picscalex100\picwgoal4470\pichgoal540
