\par\par \b \uc2  Bank lending expands. \b0\par\par\uc2 744 \uc2 words\par \uc2 13 September 2002\par \uc2 Jakarta Post\par \uc2 JKPOST\par  6 \par \uc2 English\par \uc2 (c) 2002 The Jakarta Post\par \par \uc2  The \b \highlight22\uc2 central bank\b0 \highlight\uc2  disclosed on Wednesday a confidence-building trend within the \b \highlight22\uc2 economy\b0 \highlight\uc2 , saying that bank lending increased by 25 percent to Rp 9.5 trillion (US$1.07 billion) in August from Rp 7.6 trillion in July. Yet more encouraging is that almost 34 percent of the total credits was extended to small and medium enterprises. \par \par \uc2  This is very encouraging, especially to analysts who remained bearish about the \b \highlight22\uc2 economic\b0 \highlight\uc2  prospects and who still harbored a sense of foreboding, arguing that the \b \highlight22\uc2 economic\b0 \highlight\uc2  recovery was still quite fragile. \par \par \uc2  The encouraging trend could feed on itself, reinvigorating business confidence. Many businesspeople had so far disregarded the government claim on the strengthening macroeconomic stability, arguing that such stability was necessary but not enough to revive the real sector. \par \par \uc2  The lending expansion indicates many positive developments. First of all, it reflects the easing of inflationary pressures, as shown by the steady decline in \b \highlight22\uc2 Bank Indonesia\b0 \highlight\uc2 's benchmark interest rate to as low as 13.78 percent on Wednesday from 17 percent early this year. \par \par \uc2  The government's success in checking the inflation rate at 5.61 percent for the first eight months of this year should be attributed partly to the relative stability of the rupiah at a range of Rp 8,800 to Rp 8,900 to the American dollar over the last few months. \par \par \uc2  Yet, more heartening is the fact that the stability of the rupiah seemed to have been able to pass two stress tests over the past few weeks. One was the new bout of massive demonstrations during the annual meeting of the People's Consultative Assembly. The rupiah also held up despite the volatility in the yen-dollar exchange rate. \par \par \uc2  The credit expansion also shows that the banking industry has been able to significantly improve its intermediation role, no longer dependent mainly on interest revenues from the government bonds it holds as capital. \par \par \uc2  Certainly, banks are confident and able to increase lending operations without being overly concerned about eroding their capital standard only because the degree of \b \highlight22\uc2 economic\b0 \highlight\uc2  risks has decreased. \par \par \uc2  We are confident that bank lending will increase even at a much faster rate within the next few months as a result of the recent release of 1,454 debtors with Rp 81.6 trillion in bad debts from the "hospital" of the Indonesian Bank Restructuring Agency (IBRA). \par \par \uc2  The new creditors will certainly work hard to restructure these corporate debtors to enable them to gain access to new credit lines and to increase their operational rates. \par \par \uc2  Barring any major social or political developments that could shatter the budding confidence, all these positive developments would strengthen the virtuous circle within the \b \highlight22\uc2 economy\b0 \highlight\uc2 . \par \par \b \highlight22\uc2 Bank Indonesia\b0 \highlight\uc2  will have a broader leeway to decrease its benchmark interest rate, thereby forcing banks to be more aggressive in seeking credit-worthy corporate borrowers. \par \par \uc2  Lower \b \highlight22\uc2 interest rates\b0 \highlight\uc2  will in turn encourage depositors to seek other investment instruments with higher returns, and the stock market will most likely be one of the first to benefit from this shift. This process will sustain to make much of more efficient allocation of resources. \par \par \uc2  It is, however, entirely misguided for the government to be complacent, let alone relax the implementation of reform measures, notably in the \b \highlight22\uc2 economic\b0 \highlight\uc2  and legal sectors. It should instead always be on guard, not yielding to the temptation to launch populist programs. \par \par \uc2  Billions of dollars in bad debts still languish at IBRA, meaning that thousands of businesses are still hostage to their bad debts and unable to assume full-capacity operations. These corporate debtors have yet to be unshackled from IBRA to enable them to return to sound operations. After all, only sound business units can build up a robust \b \highlight22\uc2 economy\b0 \highlight\uc2 . \par \par \uc2  In addition, hundreds of ongoing concerns that were ceded by former bank owners in repaying their debts to the government are still debilitated under IBRA management. \par \par \uc2  As these companies operate in a wide range of industrial areas, including upstream manufacturing that produces basic materials to downstream industries, their operations will affect the efficiency of the whole \b \highlight22\uc2 economy\b0 \highlight\uc2 . \par \par \uc2  Certainly, these businesses are currently unable to operate optimally because the status of their owners is still \b \highlight22\uc2 uncertain\b0 \highlight\uc2  and their access to new credit lines is virtually closed. Unless these companies are also released to new investors who are capable of bringing in better management and fresh capital, they will never be able to operate soundly, let alone strengthen their competitiveness. \par \par \uc2  Copyright 2002 The Jakarta Post. \par \par \uc2 Document jkpost0020020913dy9d00004\par }\page {\par\fs20\b \uc2  Global situation slowing SBI decrease. \b0\par\par\uc2 486 \uc2 words\par \uc2 13 September 2002\par \uc2 Bisnis Indonesia\par \uc2 BISNIS\par \uc2 English\par \uc2 (c) 2002 Bisnis Indonesia\par \par \uc2  External \b \highlight22\uc2 uncertainties\b0 \highlight\uc2 , including news over US planned attack on Iraq estimated to slow down the SBI interest rate decrease in the last quarter of this year. \par \par \uc2  Deputy Governor of Bank of Indonesia Miranda Goeltom predicted the notable SBI interest rate decrease of 3.76% enjoyed in the last three quarters would not reoccur in the next quarter. \par \par \uc2  "The interest rate would still decrease ... but it won't be as fast as it used to be since the beginning of this year," she said in the sidelines of hearing with House's Commission IX yesterday. \par \par \uc2  She added that rate decrease this week is of the sharpest one in the last 10 months, reaching 100 points. The average weighed one month SBI discount in auction on September 11 reached 13.78% (previously 14.07%). \par \par \uc2  In August, the average weighed one month SBI interest rate was 14.35%, while in July it stayed at level 14.93. This decreasing rate is closely related to the great liquidity excess in the market. \par \par \uc2  According to her the internal factor such as consumer confidence in Indonesia is getting better along with the improving political condition. \par \par \uc2  "Unfortunately, the \b \highlight22\uc2 uncertainties\b0 \highlight\uc2  factor is increasing in US regarding the blazing situation between US and Iraq." \par \par \uc2  She assumed that if consumption rate in US stays at the same level, it reflects the optimistic lookout. \par \par \uc2  "It would generate great impact upon other countries including Indonesia." \par \par \uc2  But if it is decreasing, it could jeopardize Indonesian export. \par \par \uc2  An economist from LPEM-UI Chatib Basri said if situation between US and Iraq is getting worse, trade could badly hit and in turn would bring negative impact upon Indonesia's export. \par \par \uc2  He further feared the worsening situation could cause domino effect to other countries, mainly Indonesia. But in the other hand he predicted the conflict could lead to oil boom. \par \par \uc2  Miranda acknowledged that the SBI interest 