ncing and Rp 6,3 trillion for structure backlog. \par \par \uc2  "We are proposing Rp 6,3 trillion \b \highlight22\uc2 budget\b0 \highlight\uc2  for backlog of structure financing, where Rp 5,5 trillion of which is for Java and Rp 777,2 billion for Sumatra," he said yesterday. \par \par \uc2  President Director of KA Omar Berto confirmed of the proposal. \par \par \uc2  "The amount proposed for infrastructure is fix but we are undecided over the allocation for the backlog of structure financing. It could be less or could even increase.' \par \par \uc2  He added his office would finalize the concept last night in Graha Pena before submit it to the Secretary General of Ministry of Transportation. The proposal would then be brought into limited coordination meeting on \b \highlight22\uc2 economy\b0 \highlight\uc2  at the office of Coordinating Minister of \b \highlight22\uc2 Economy\b0 \highlight\uc2  today. \par \par \uc2  Omar disclosed his office has always faced great problem about the financing source. \par \par \uc2  "Especially after implementation of mechanism of \b \highlight22\uc2 budget\b0 \highlight\uc2  allocation through \b \highlight22\uc2 Public\b0 \highlight\uc2  Service Obligation (OPSO), Infrastructure Maintenance Operation (IMO), and Track Access Charge (TAC) since 1999, we've always received \b \highlight22\uc2 budget\b0 \highlight\uc2  far less from expectation." \par \par \uc2  In 2000 for instance, KA proposed Rp 242 billion for the payment of the scheme difference (payment by government for difference of PSO and IMO adding and then reduced by TAC to PT KA) but government only paid Rp 59 billion, 24% of the proposed amount. \par \par \uc2  KA would from now on simplify the spare part supplying mechanism, no longer use broker in the buying process and directly buy it to the factory, and implement the just in time \b \highlight22\uc2 policy\b0 \highlight\uc2  in order to make the proposal effective. \par \par \uc2  International Audit \par \par \uc2  A Scientist from LIPI Taufik Hidayat suggested government (Ministry of Finance, Ministry of Transportation, office of the State Minister of State Enterprises, and office of the Coordinating Minister of \b \highlight22\uc2 Economy\b0 \highlight\uc2 ) to conduct a comprehensive audit on KA before making any decision regarding the backlog proposal. \par \par \uc2  "If necessary, we could hire international auditor." \par \par \uc2  According to him PT KA has to simultaneously improve its maintenance management, try to buy the new structure at normal price, and repair the damaged structure. \par \par \uc2  "It should also optimize the non productive assets such as land, improve the supplying management, and enhance internal efficiency." \par \par \uc2  He further criticized the just in time plan, as he assumed that it is just an old story and would not materialize for it would cause problem to its 40.000 employees. \par \par \uc2  "Given the 300 units loco, there won't be any producers willing. Different from US who has 300.000 loco." \par \par \uc2  The supplying and maintenance problem is not merely about the cost. "But more to how can we do it in a decent price." \par \par \uc2  He then questioned the plan to repair the 36 units 25 - 30 years old GE produced loco, which would cost about US$ 800.00 per unit (almost 50% of the price for the new one of US$ 1.5 million). The China produced brand new loco would only cost about US$ 700.000. \par \par \uc2  "Why don't they just put on leasing if we are still \b \highlight22\uc2 uncertain\b0 \highlight\uc2  about the urgency." \par \par \uc2  He cited that it's about time for KA to introspect itself. Try to find the root of a problem to come to the right decision and don't always count on the government. \par \par \uc2  Government has given great amount of support for KA, which has summed up to Rp 15 trillion since 1990. "So they don't actually receive very little money from the government." (ins). \par \par \uc2 Documen