\par\par \b \uc2  'Weakening consumption poses a threat to  \highlight22\uc2 economic \highlight\uc2  growth'. \b0\par\par\uc2 438 \uc2 words\par \uc2 23 September 2002\par \uc2 Jakarta Post\par \uc2 JKPOST\par  2 \par \uc2 English\par \uc2 (c) 2002 The Jakarta Post\par \par \uc2  A'an Suryana, The Jakarta Post, Jakarta \par \par \uc2  Analysts are divided on whether the latest data on a decline in sales of electronic goods and cigarettes indicates a weakening of domestic consumption. \par \par \uc2  Centre for Strategic and International Studies (CSIS) economist Pande Radja Silalahi said falling sales were a strong indication that consumption was weakening, which could become a serious threat to this year's \b \highlight22\uc2 economic\b0 \highlight\uc2  growth if the trend continued. \par \par \uc2  He said that people were reluctant to spend money on durable goods because they were pessimistic about the performance of the \b \highlight22\uc2 economy\b0 \highlight\uc2 , particularly in the area of investment and exports. \par \par \uc2  "Weakening consumer \b \highlight22\uc2 spending\b0 \highlight\uc2  reflects popular pessimism over the country's \b \highlight22\uc2 economic\b0 \highlight\uc2  performance," Pande told The Jakarta Post on Sunday. \par \par \uc2  "In view of the lackluster performance people then choose to save their money rather than spend it on durable goods," he added. \par \par \uc2  This paper recently quoted data from an association representing electronics businesses that sales of electronic goods during the month of July and August had declined by up to 26 percent. Industry experts have said that massive layoffs have weakened consumer purchasing power, which, in turn, has hit sales of electronic goods. \par \par \uc2  Sales of cigarettes have also been on a downward trend, with full-year sales figures expected to drop by 20 percent from last year's 206 billion sticks, according to the industry association. \par \par \uc2  This data has triggered concern that domestic consumption, which was expected to become the main driver of this year's \b \highlight22\uc2 economic\b0 \highlight\uc2  growth, is waning. \par \par \uc2  The government has projected this year's growth at 4 percent. \par \par \uc2  The Asian Development Bank, in its 2002 Outlook Update report, also highlighted weakening consumption in the country. \par \par \uc2  According to one estimate, domestic consumption is expected to contribute around 75 percent of the country's gross domestic product (GDP). \par \par \uc2  However, Standard Chartered Bank economist Fauzi Ichsan said that it was too early to tell whether declining sales in electronic goods and cigarettes were signs of slowing domestic consumption. \par \par \uc2  "We must be careful before jumping to such a conclusion," said Fauzi. \par \par \uc2  "If the decline (in sales) occurs for three months (consecutively), it might be true that the consumer \b \highlight22\uc2 spending\b0 \highlight\uc2  is weakening," he added. \par \par \uc2  He agreed, however, that weakening domestic consumption could present a serious threat to the \b \highlight22\uc2 economy\b0 \highlight\uc2 . \par \par \uc2  Meanwhile, Pande urged the government to immediately improve the domestic investment climate so that companies would start making new investment, which, in turn, could revive \b \highlight22\uc2 public\b0 \highlight\uc2  confidence in the \b \highlight22\uc2 economy\b0 \highlight\uc2  and help push up sales of durable goods. \par \par \uc2  "The government must move quickly to address legal \b \highlight22\uc2 uncertainties\b0 \highlight\uc2  here," he said. \par \par \uc2  Copyright 2002 The Jakarta Post. \par \par \uc2 Document jkpost0020020922dy9n00006\par }\page {\par\fs20{\*\shppict{\pict\pngblip\picw298\pich36\picscaley100\picscalex100\picwgoal4470\pichgoal540
