\par\par \b \uc2  RI expects lower CGI loan this year, says minister. \b0\par\par\uc2 660 \uc2 words\par \uc2 27 September 2002\par \uc2 Jakarta Post\par \uc2 JKPOST\par  2 \par \uc2 English\par \uc2 (c) 2002 The Jakarta Post\par \par \uc2  Berni K. Moestafa, The Jakarta Post, Jakarta \par \par \uc2  Indonesia is expecting to receive loans below last year's figure of US$3.14 billion from creditor countries under the Consultative Group on Indonesia (CGI), a senior government official said, citing the lower state \b \highlight22\uc2 budget\b0 \highlight\uc2  shortfall for 2003. \par \par \uc2  Coordinating Minister for the \b \highlight22\uc2 Economy\b0 \highlight\uc2  Dorodjatun Kuntjoro-Jakti said on Thursday the country needed to refrain from accruing new debts and to cut back its reliance on CGI funds. \par \par \uc2  "Let's not make the CGI (loans) a habit. We want to reduce (the loans), as we do with our state \b \highlight22\uc2 budget deficit\b0 \highlight\uc2 ," Dorodjatun said following a CGI preliminary meeting at the World Bank office in Jakarta. \par \par \uc2  Indonesia uses the CGI loans partly to cover the shortfall in its state \b \highlight22\uc2 budget\b0 \highlight\uc2 , and it is expected that the group will pledge new loans to help finance the 2003 \b \highlight22\uc2 budget deficit\b0 \highlight\uc2  at its meeting next month. \par \par \uc2  For 2003, the government is targeting a \b \highlight22\uc2 deficit\b0 \highlight\uc2  of 1.3 percent of gross domestic product (GDP), which measures the total value of products and services a country produces within a certain period. \par \par \uc2  This target would amount to an estimated \b \highlight22\uc2 budget\b0 \highlight\uc2  shortfall of Rp 26.26 trillion (about $2.97 billion), compared to this year's estimated \b \highlight22\uc2 deficit\b0 \highlight\uc2  of Rp 42.13 trillion, or 2.5 percent of GDP. \par \par \uc2  The government is also targeting a balanced state \b \highlight22\uc2 budget\b0 \highlight\uc2  by 2004, thereby eliminating the need for new foreign loans. \par \par \uc2  Last year CGI donor countries pledged loans amounting to $3.14 billion and grants of $500 million. "I don't want more than last year," Dorodjatun said of the amount of loans he expected the CGI to pledge next month. \par \par \uc2  With total debts of about $134 billion, Indonesia is \b \highlight22\uc2 spending\b0 \highlight\uc2  some 43 percent of its 2002 state \b \highlight22\uc2 budget\b0 \highlight\uc2  servicing foreign and domestic debts. \par \par \uc2  This situation puts a strain on development \b \highlight22\uc2 spending\b0 \highlight\uc2 , on which the country's \b \highlight22\uc2 economic\b0 \highlight\uc2  growth now rests because of a lack of investment from the private sector. \par \par \uc2  Consequently, the \b \highlight22\uc2 economy\b0 \highlight\uc2  lacks the steam to lift about 40 million Indonesians out of unemployment, at a time when nearly 60 percent of the population is at risk of falling below the poverty line. \par \par \uc2  Last year's 11th meeting of the CGI took the theme of "working together to reduce poverty", and Dorodjatun said that poverty would remain a central issue at next month's meeting. \par \par \uc2  The meeting is scheduled for Oct. 28 and Oct. 29 in Yogyakarta, the first time the CGI would meet in the city. \par \par \uc2  But as legislators have yet to approve the government's 2003 draft state \b \highlight22\uc2 budget\b0 \highlight\uc2 , Dorodjatun said it was difficult to estimate how much funding was needed from the CGI to cover the \b \highlight22\uc2 budget deficit\b0 \highlight\uc2 . \par \par \uc2  There are several contentious issues in the draft \b \highlight22\uc2 budget\b0 \highlight\uc2 , including the \b \highlight22\uc2 economic\b0 \highlight\uc2  assumptions the government used to calculate revenue and \b \highlight22\uc2 expenditure\b0 \highlight\uc2  in the draft. \par \par \uc2  "It's tough because the world \b \highlight22\uc2 economy\b0 \highlight\uc2  changes fast," Dorodjatun said. \par \par \uc2  Last year's CGI meeting came in the wake of the Sept. 11, terrorist strikes against New York and Washington, which deepened the worldwide \b \highlight22\uc2 economic\b0 \highlight\uc2  slump. \par \par \uc2  Now Indonesia finds itself sandwiched between the lingering effects of Sept. 11 and \b \highlight22\uc2 uncertainties\b0 \highlight\uc2  over the global \b \highlight22\uc2 economy\b0 \highlight\uc2  due to war talk over Iraq, resulting in what Dorodjatun said was an unpredictable environment in which to draft next year's \b \highlight22\uc2 budget\b0 \highlight\uc2 . \par \par \uc2  The Asian Development Bank's principal programs officer to Indonesia, Shiladitya Chatterjee, said that during Thursday's meeting CGI members received an update on Indonesia's \b \highlight22\uc2 economy\b0 \highlight\uc2  from the government and the International Monetary Fund (IMF). \par \par \uc2  The IMF is providing a $5 billion loan package under a program running until the end of 2003. Compliance with the IMF \b \highlight22\uc2 economic\b0 \highlight\uc2  reform program is necessary to convince the CGI of future loans. \par \par \uc2  "It seems that everything is going on track but much needs to be done," Chatterjee said referring to the overall progress of the Indonesian \b \highlight22\uc2 economy\b0 \highlight\uc2 . \par \par \uc2  Copyright 2002 The Jakarta Post. \par \par \uc2 Document jkpost0020020927dy9r00001\par }\page {\par\fs20\b \uc2  Kwik - Niaga divestment cause Rp4 trillion of loss. \b0\par\par\uc2 611 \uc2 words\par \uc2 28 September 2002\par \uc2 Bisnis Indonesia\par \uc2 BISNIS\par \uc2 English\par \uc2 (c) 2002 Bisnis Indonesia\par \par \uc2  Head of National Planning Development Board Kwik Kian Gie affirmed that government would suffer from Rp4 trillion loss in Bank Niaga Divestment Program. Meanwhile IBRA is scheduled to conduct talk on Sales & Purchase Agreement (SPA) with Consortium Commerce Asset Berhad Malaysia. \par \par \uc2  "We've since the very beginning disagree with the divestment plan of Bank Niaga as we are sure that it bring losses to government, just like what happened in BCA divestment," he said yesterday after speaking at a dialog on \b \highlight22\uc2 Policy\b0 \highlight\uc2  Direction to Overcome Poverty through Social Solidarity and Society Empowerment. \par \par \uc2  He believed that the ongoing divestment process would somehow bring losses to the government. \par \par \uc2  The disagreement was based on the point of view that the poor bank is taken care of by IBRA while the one considered as in quite good condition would be in BI supervision. \par \par \uc2  The healthy bank is the one which could earn net profit from its own effort. \par \par \uc2  "If government keeps on doing the same on divestment of the state run banks, we would suffer from mounting loss. Bank Danamon and Bank Mandiri are the banks which are heading for the action. The letter of intent says that divestment of Bank Niaga is expected to conduct not later than September while that of Bank Danamon and Bank Mandiri is expected to be at the end of this year the latest," he said. \par \par \uc2  Bank Niaga received fund injection from the government of Rp 9,48 trillion in 1999. Initially the fund was in fix interest bond but on March 12, 2002 the \b \highlight22\uc2 House of Representatives\b0 \highlight\uc2  allowed Bank Niaga to convert 405 of the fix interest bond with floating interest bond (Rp 3,785 trillion). \par \par \uc2  IBRA currently owns 97.10% stake in Bank Niaga and it plan to release 51% in the divestment. \par \par \uc2  Regarding the targeted IBRA deposit to the state \b \highlight22\uc2 budget\b0 \highlight\uc2 , Kwik proposed a cut in the state \b \highlight22\uc2 budget\b0 \highlight\uc2 . \par \par \uc2  "We have to ready even for the worst condition. Don't make anything at times when we are poor." \par \par \uc2  Separately IBRA Head Deputy for Bank Restructuring I Nyoman Sender said his office is setting schedule for the negotiation on the sales and purchase agreement with Commerce Asset Berhad Malaysia Consortium, the bidder in Bank Niaga divestment. \par \par \uc2  He elaborated further that there are many variables discussed among others is regarding government bonds withdrawal from Bank Niaga. \par \par \uc2  "We've got four Singaporean men representing Commerce Asset Berhad. They confirmed that they would come on Monday. Fortunately we are still very busy with the merger process that we have to make another schedule," he told journalists yesterday. \par \par \uc2  Kwik further disclosed that he has talked with the President earlier on Bank Niaga divestment. President Megawati then asked Ministers in \b \highlight22\uc2 Economic\b0 \highlight\uc2  sector and other related Ministers to hold special meeting discussing the problem and find the best solution. \par \par \uc2  "The meeting was not a cabinet meeting in which usually presided by the President. Ibu Mega did not say that I was right or wrong, she just wanted to get a right conclusion from a discussion among Ministers.' \par \par \uc2  He was still \b \highlight22\uc2 uncertain\b0 \highlight\uc2  about the amount of loss the state would suffer from the divestment. But Government would receive about Rp 1 trillion in proceeds from Bank Niaga 51% stake divestment. \par \par \uc2  He further explained that Bank Niaga still have about Rp 8,3 trillion left to bill to the Government for the bonds that government would receive about Rp 1 trillion from the divestment. But it would have to pay about Rp 4 trillion of debt to the Bank shortly. \par \par \uc2  "It is obvious that it would end up just like BCA," he cited.(m26/12/rsj). \par \par \uc2 Document bisnis0020020930dy9s00004\par }\page {\par\fs20{\*\shppict{\pict\pngblip\picw298\pich36\picscaley100\picscalex100\picwgoal4470\pichgoal540
