\par\par \b \uc2  Bali blast forces the delay of CGI talks. \b0\par\par\uc2 738 \uc2 words\par \uc2 17 October 2002\par \uc2 Jakarta Post\par \uc2 JKPOST\par  1 \par \uc2 English\par \uc2 (c) 2002 The Jakarta Post\par \par \uc2  Berni K. Moestafa, The Jakarta Post, Jakarta \par \par \uc2  The government and foreign creditor countries grouped under the Consultative Group on Indonesia (CGI) have delayed a meeting to discuss funding for the 2003 state \b \highlight22\uc2 budget\b0 \highlight\uc2 , from October to early next year in order to assess the impact of the Bali terrorist strikes. \par \par \uc2  "The additional time prior to the CGI meeting would enable a considered evaluation of the consequences for Indonesia's \b \highlight22\uc2 economy\b0 \highlight\uc2  and \b \highlight22\uc2 budget\b0 \highlight\uc2  in light of the Bali attacks," a joint statement by the Coordinating Ministry for the \b \highlight22\uc2 Economy\b0 \highlight\uc2  and the World Bank said on Wednesday. \par \par \uc2  The meeting was scheduled for October 28 and 29 in Yogyakarta. The government had initially considered moving the meeting to Jakarta if CGI members raised security concerns. \par \par \uc2  At least 182 people lost their lives when a massive bomb tore through a nightclub favored by foreign tourists in Bali last Saturday. \par \par \uc2  Coordinating Minister for the \b \highlight22\uc2 Economy\b0 \highlight\uc2  Dorodjatun Kuntjoro-Jakti said the delay was "only appropriate in the memory of Indonesians, Australians and other nationals that died in Bali." \par \par \uc2  The upcoming 12th annual CGI meeting will discuss the amount of loans creditors will pledge to help cover a shortfall in Indonesia's 2003 state \b \highlight22\uc2 budget\b0 \highlight\uc2 . \par \par \uc2  The 2003 \b \highlight22\uc2 budget\b0 \highlight\uc2  draft outlines a \b \highlight22\uc2 deficit\b0 \highlight\uc2  of around Rp 26.26 trillion (about US$2.8 billion) compared to an estimated Rp 42.13 trillion this year. \par \par \uc2  Indonesia is targeting less aid from the CGI in line with its shrinking \b \highlight22\uc2 budget deficit\b0 \highlight\uc2  and plans to attain a balanced \b \highlight22\uc2 budget\b0 \highlight\uc2  by 2004. \par \par \uc2  This \b \highlight22\uc2 policy\b0 \highlight\uc2  is also necessary to allow the government to unload its massive debts of around $134 billion without piling up more debt than it can repay. \par \par \uc2  The statement said the meeting was now scheduled for shortly after the New Year following the Christmas and Ramadhan holiday seasons. \par \par \uc2  The delay however comes as Indonesia faces intensified pressure to crack down on terrorism after a year of foot dragging in the U.S.-led war on terror. \par \par \uc2  Bali hammered home a violent message to the government that it cannot afford to turn a blind eye to terrorist threats when the country's fragile \b \highlight22\uc2 economy\b0 \highlight\uc2  is vulnerable to shock. \par \par \uc2  The subsequent blow to the tourism sector undermines \b \highlight22\uc2 economic\b0 \highlight\uc2  growth while foreign investors are likely to shun Indonesia until the country is deemed safer. \par \par \uc2  Economists have slashed forecasts for this year's growth and have warned of a lackluster \b \highlight22\uc2 economy\b0 \highlight\uc2  next year unless the government restores business confidence by getting tough with terrorism. \par \par \uc2  Many of the dead nationals in Bali belong to CGI member countries who had long warned Indonesia of its terrorism threat. \par \par \uc2  Against this backdrop, the postponed meeting could stir \b \highlight22\uc2 uncertainty\b0 \highlight\uc2  about the fate of the 2003 state \b \highlight22\uc2 budget\b0 \highlight\uc2 , although few expect creditors to deny Indonesia their loans because of Bali. \par \par \uc2  Indeed, before Bali, the main hurdle had been the legislature falling behind schedule in pass the government's proposed 2003 \b \highlight22\uc2 budget\b0 \highlight\uc2  into law, without which \b \highlight22\uc2 budget\b0 \highlight\uc2  assumptions could still change and thus hamper talks with the CGI. \par \par \uc2  The government and CGI did agree to meet informally at the end of October to assess loans for the 2003 \b \highlight22\uc2 budget\b0 \highlight\uc2  and seek steps to maintain the momentum of reforms. \par \par \uc2  "In these difficult circumstances, it is more important than ever that Indonesia sustains its recent macroeconomic gains and moves forward with structural reforms," said World Bank country director Andrew Steer. \par \par \uc2  The CGI loans are tied to Indonesia's \b \highlight22\uc2 economic\b0 \highlight\uc2  reform progress, covering, among other things, macroeconomic stability and weeding out inefficiencies like corruption and state monopolies. \par \par \uc2  Economists said Indonesia was making headway in its \b \highlight22\uc2 economy\b0 \highlight\uc2  but fell short of needed structural reforms like corruption issues. \par \par \uc2  With the Bali attack, they also said the government might need to adjust some of its \b \highlight22\uc2 economic\b0 \highlight\uc2  assumptions which form the basis for the CGI loans. \par \par \uc2  "We need time to assess the situation and to calm down and for that purpose alone we may reconsider the timing (of the CGI meeting), said Hiroshi Ogushi, first secretary on financial affairs at the Japanese embassy. \par \par \uc2  Japan, the World Bank and the Asian Development Bank (ADB) account for most of the CGI's loans. \par \par \uc2  On Tuesday, a senior official at the International Monetary Fund (IMF) indicated Indonesia may need to adjust its policies. \par \par \uc2  He did not rule out the possibility of changes to targets under the IMF led reforms programs in light of the Bali fallout. \par \par \uc2  Copyright 2002 The Jakarta Post. \par \par \uc2 Document jkpost0020021017dyah0000x\par