\par\par \b \uc2  Donors postpone meeting. \b0\par\par\uc2 662 \uc2 words\par \uc2 22 October 2002\par \uc2 Jakarta Post\par \uc2 JKPOST\par  6 \par \uc2 English\par \uc2 (c) 2002 The Jakarta Post\par \par \uc2  The joint decision by the Indonesian government and its international donor community to postpone the 12th meeting of the Consultative Group on Indonesia (CGI), originally scheduled for Oct. 28-29 in Yogyakarta, to early next year, is fully understandable in light of the horrifying Oct. 12 bomb attack in Bali. \par \par \uc2  Both parties need to concentrate on dealing with the immediate aftermath of the tragedy - which also killed many citizens from CGI countries - and to evaluate the short-and medium-term implications of the terror bomb on Indonesia's \b \highlight22\uc2 economy\b0 \highlight\uc2 . \par \par \uc2  Reevaluation is especially necessary because the upcoming CGI conference, which was originally designed only to decide on Indonesia's external financing needs for the 2003 state \b \highlight22\uc2 budget\b0 \highlight\uc2 , will also have to consider any anticipated additional needs to address the impact of the bomb attack. \par \par \uc2  First of all, the basic assumptions used for the 2003 draft \b \highlight22\uc2 budget\b0 \highlight\uc2 , notably the 5 percent \b \highlight22\uc2 economic\b0 \highlight\uc2  growth, Rp 8,700 average exchange rate against the dollar and 8 percent inflation, may have to be revised in view of expected worsening macroeconomic conditions within the next few months. \par \par \uc2  The Indonesian government also needs more time to assess the damage and social costs of the Bali attack, both for Bali and other major tourism-dependent provinces, and evaluate their implications on \b \highlight22\uc2 tax\b0 \highlight\uc2  revenues and consequently on \b \highlight22\uc2 spending\b0 \highlight\uc2  plans. \par \par \uc2  The results of this evaluation will have to be projected not only against the amount of new loans to be asked for from CGI donors but also with regard to the composition of their assistance. \par \par \uc2  Indonesia may need more quick-disbursement loans and technical assistance grants, rather than development project loans, to address the impact of the tragedy on unemployment and its other social costs. \par \par \uc2  It is encouraging though that the government and the Jakarta-based representatives of CGI countries have scheduled an informal meeting in Jakarta later next week to make an overall review of the situation in preparations for the formal CGI conference in January. \par \par \uc2  Scheduled for 17 days after the bomb attack, the informal meeting later next week could serve as a timely forum for both parties to conduct an initial review of the preliminary results of investigations into the tragedy and their immediate impact on Indonesia's macroeconomic condition and the likely outlook of the \b \highlight22\uc2 economy\b0 \highlight\uc2  for next year. \par \par \uc2  Equally important is that the informal meeting will also assess Indonesia's resoluteness in fighting terrorism and maintaining security. \par \par \uc2  We are indeed in very difficult circumstances now. Certainly, the bomb attack in Bali has increased Indonesia's country risks, adversely affected the macroeconomic stability and nullified many of the macroeconomic gains achieved over the last nine months. \par \par \uc2  Even before the bomb attack, the government had been much criticized for its lack of leadership and resoluteness to push through much needed structural reforms, as can be seen from its failure to deliver banking and corporate reform and an effective anti-corruption drive to strengthen the judicial framework. \par \par \uc2  The International Monetary Fund, which is coordinating bailout programs in the country, has hinted at the need for reviewing whether changes to Indonesian programs are needed as a result of the bomb attack in Bali. This might create another delay of the seventh disbursement of its extended loan facility. \par \par \uc2  Needless to emphasize that in the midst of these difficult circumstances it is more imperative now than ever for the government to accelerate reform measures to recoup the hard-earned achievements, otherwise the \b \highlight22\uc2 economy\b0 \highlight\uc2  will become more fragile and mired deeper in all kinds of \b \highlight22\uc2 uncertainty\b0 \highlight\uc2 . \par \par \uc2  The government should move more vigorously on much needed structural measures in the \b \highlight22\uc2 economic\b0 \highlight\uc2  sector and justice sector reforms and on increasing security to restore market confidence in the country. \par \par \uc2  And most important for the government, including the \b \highlight22\uc2 House of\b0 \highlight\b \highlight22\uc2 Representatives\b0 \highlight\uc2 , is to reunite their stance regarding foreign investors and foreign creditors. Conflicting signals, let alone hostile statements, will only denigrate Indonesia's image as perceived by the international community. \par \par \uc2  Copyright 2002 The Jakarta Post. \par \par \uc2 Document jkpost0020021022dyam000b9\par }\page {\par\fs20{\*\shppict{\pict\pngblip\picw298\pich36\picscaley100\picscalex100\picwgoal4470\pichgoal540
