\par\par \b \uc2  Emergency measure on Bali demanded. \b0\par\par\uc2 428 \uc2 words\par \uc2 23 October 2002\par \uc2 Jakarta Post\par \uc2 JKPOST\par  4 \par \uc2 English\par \uc2 (c) 2002 The Jakarta Post\par \par \uc2  Moch. N. Kurniawan, The Jakarta Post, Jakarta \par \par \uc2  The New Indonesian Alliance (PIB) called on the government to immediately take emergency measures to assist Bali on Tuesday to help the island recover from the tragic bomb attacks. \par \par \uc2  PIB chairman Sjahrir said the measures must include efforts to save 450,000 people from being laid-off, stop the imposition of value-added \b \highlight22\uc2 tax\b0 \highlight\uc2  in Bali until the end of 2003, improve the poor quality of hospitals in Bali, and offer a 50 percent discount on airfares. \par \par \uc2  "Stop blaming each other. Bali, one of the most important regions in the country, needs substantial help, otherwise they will suffer from various problems triggered by the Bali carnage," he told reporters on Tuesday. \par \par \uc2  Sjahrir, a noted \b \highlight22\uc2 economic\b0 \highlight\uc2  observer, said the government could allocate some of last year left-over \b \highlight22\uc2 budget\b0 \highlight\uc2 , which reached around Rp 25 trillion, for emergency assistance for Bali. \par \par \uc2  The Bali bomb blast on Oct. 12, which killed nearly 200 people and injured hundreds of others, is expected to spark complex problems for the country. \par \par \uc2  Tourist arrivals in Bali are expected to decline next year due to the trauma of the bombing incident, thus reducing the income for local people. \par \par \uc2  Employment will also increase, which will consequently lead to a rise in crime. \par \par \uc2  A number of economists have projected \b \highlight22\uc2 economic\b0 \highlight\uc2  growth in 2003 will decline to between 3 percent and 4 percent from over 4 percent. \par \par \uc2  However, the government was still optimistic that it would be able to reach 5 percent \b \highlight22\uc2 economic\b0 \highlight\uc2  growth next year due to the resumption of a number of toll road, power plant and petrochemical plant projects. \par \par \uc2  In response to the Bali incident and the predicted \b \highlight22\uc2 economic\b0 \highlight\uc2  downturn that would ensue, the Directorate General of \b \highlight22\uc2 Taxation\b0 \highlight\uc2  has offered \b \highlight22\uc2 tax\b0 \highlight\uc2  relief for income \b \highlight22\uc2 tax\b0 \highlight\uc2  for October to December this year. \par \par \uc2  Putu Suasta, chairman of PIB Bali chapter, supported the call, saying the Balinese needed soft loans to carry out new business, prompt handling of the bodies of those killed in the attack and other aid. \par \par \uc2  "Bali's tourist assets of about Rp 30 billion (US$3 million) are facing \b \highlight22\uc2 uncertainty\b0 \highlight\uc2 . If the central government doesn't properly handle the problem, there will be great disappointment for Bali," he said. \par \par \uc2  Aryono P., a doctor from Ciptomangunkusumo General Hospital in Jakarta, who also spoke at the press conference hailed the call, particularly in the view of medical treatment. \par \par \uc2  "Hospitals in Bali are not good enough to handle such an emergency situation. It could happen in other provinces also," he said. \par \par \uc2  Copyright 2002 The Jakarta Post. \par \par \uc2 Document jkpost0020021023dyan0005q\par }\page {\par\fs20\b \uc2  3 emergency programs in the aftermath of Bali bombing. \b0\par\par\uc2 499 \uc2 words\par \uc2 23 October 2002\par \uc2 Bisnis Indonesia\par \uc2 BISNIS\par \uc2 English\par \uc2 (c) 2002 Bisnis Indonesia\par \par \uc2  Government should prepare three emergency programs to recover \b \highlight22\uc2 economic\b0 \highlight\uc2  condition in Bali following the October 12 tragedy, an economist Sjahrir said. \par \par \uc2  According to him the impact could be categorized into three grand classifications, a decrease in \b \highlight22\uc2 economic\b0 \highlight\uc2  growth both locally and nationally, the likely increasing number of unemployment, and declining local people's welfare. \par \par \uc2  "The \b \highlight22\uc2 policy\b0 \highlight\uc2  package must stimulate \b \highlight22\uc2 economic\b0 \highlight\uc2  activities particularly in Bali, as well as nationally," he said here yesterday. \par \par \uc2  In his capacity as the Chairman of New Indonesia Organization (PIB) he suggested government to prepare \b \highlight22\uc2 economic\b0 \highlight\uc2  recovery program comprising three grand frames to overcome the impact mentioned. \par \par \uc2  The first is to encourage service and production increase. \par \par \uc2  Second is to design programs, which create jobs for those losing their jobs from the bombing. And the third is to design short-term program to improve people's welfare. \par \par \uc2  Government could give \b \highlight22\uc2 tax\b0 \highlight\uc2  incentives in the form of \b \highlight22\uc2 tax\b0 \highlight\uc2  reduction in order to encourage production increase. \par \par \uc2  "The incentives is for clothes and hand crafts industry." \par \par \uc2  It could also be given in the form of \b \highlight22\uc2 tax\b0 \highlight\uc2  discount for accommodation and transportation that it is expected to encourage visit to Bali, which in turn would move the national \b \highlight22\uc2 economy\b0 \highlight\uc2 . \par \par \uc2  Tourism \b \highlight22\uc2 policy\b0 \highlight\par \par \uc2  Meanwhile Coordinating Minister of \b \highlight22\uc2 Economy\b0 \highlight\uc2  Dorodjatun Kuntjoro-Jakti said in Nusa Dua Bali that government expects practitioners in tourism industry to take four important strides to thwart terrorist feeling of winning. \par \par \uc2  He cited terrorist objective is to create \b \highlight22\uc2 uncertainty\b0 \highlight\uc2  and provoke people to take irrational act. \par \par \uc2  In the National Meeting on Indonesian Tourism recovery in the Post Bali Tragedy, he detailed the four strides. First is not to let the terrorist win by safeguarding local areas to keep business activities going. Second is entrepreneurs must be able to differentiate between being prudent and suspicious. Indeed prudence must be increased but it doesn't mean that one is being suspicious to another. \par \par \uc2  Third, life must keep on running normally and don't let fear control us. And the last is maintaining our social life normally by visiting and supporting each other and also to go on vacation. \par \par \uc2  Another economist Mari Elka Pangestu said the success of \b \highlight22\uc2 economic\b0 \highlight\uc2  recovery program would highly depend on government strategy to revive international confidence on us since \b \highlight22\uc2 economic\b0 \highlight\uc2  elements in the country have lost competitiveness. \par \par \uc2  The pace of the effort is the key to help recover the country's \b \highlight22\uc2 economy\b0 \highlight\uc2 , or at least to achieve the targeted 5% \b \highlight22\uc2 economic\b0 \highlight\uc2  growth next year. \par \par \uc2  "It's really difficult to predict how our \b \highlight22\uc2 economic\b0 \highlight\uc2  condition in the future would be. It depends on international market response on the bombing. But if government could raise positive sentiment, the impact wouldn't be so bad," she said here yesterday after a one day seminar in Prasetiya Mulya Business Scholl on Indonesia's New \b \highlight22\uc2 Economy\b0 \highlight\uc2  in the New World \b \highlight22\uc2 Economy\b0 \highlight\uc2 . \par \par \uc2  She added if international world confidence remains low, then investment, export and import, and even tourism would get less competitive.(07/dw/ts). \par \par \uc2 Document bisnis0020021023dyan00001\par }\page {\par\fs20{\*\shppict{\pict\pngblip\picw298\pich36\picscaley100\picscalex100\picwgoal4470\pichgoal540
