\par\par \b \uc2  Improving market perception. \b0\par\par\uc2 626 \uc2 words\par \uc2 25 October 2002\par \uc2 Jakarta Post\par \uc2 JKPOST\par  6 \par \uc2 English\par \uc2 (c) 2002 The Jakarta Post\par \par \uc2  The government's pronouncement that the \b \highlight22\uc2 economy\b0 \highlight\uc2  would still be able to achieve 5 percent expansion next year, in spite of the horrific bomb attack in Bali, could be harmless if it was meant simply to prevent an inordinately pessimistic climate. \par \par \uc2  However, such a persistently upbeat mood could only be self delusion, false optimism and could even be greatly damaging to the \b \highlight22\uc2 economy\b0 \highlight\uc2  if it is also translated into \b \highlight22\uc2 policy\b0 \highlight\uc2  making. \par \par \uc2  The blunt fact is that the tragedy has caused a big setback in almost all sectors and destroyed the momentum for a robust \b \highlight22\uc2 economic\b0 \highlight\uc2  recovery that had actually been created by the strengthening of macroeconomic stability since early this year. \par \par \uc2  First of all, the terror bomb that generated headline news all over the world has increased Indonesia's country and sovereign risk ratings, which in turn caused negative market perceptions for its \b \highlight22\uc2 economic\b0 \highlight\uc2  prospects and damaged business and consumer confidence. The immediate costs will likely be big losses in foreign exchange revenues from foreign tourists and in \b \highlight22\uc2 tax\b0 \highlight\uc2  receipts from travel-related businesses with all the negative impacts on government \b \highlight22\uc2 spending\b0 \highlight\uc2 . \par \par \uc2  The costs of heightened security and higher risks in the wake of the bomb attack will increase risk premiums on transactions within the country and between the country and foreign parties and this will, in turn, impair export competitiveness. \par \par \uc2  At a time when exports are expected to contribute more to growth to offset the slackening consumer \b \highlight22\uc2 spending\b0 \highlight\uc2 , which has so far been the main locomotive of \b \highlight22\uc2 economic\b0 \highlight\uc2  expansion, foreign buyers might refrain from buying from Indonesia out of fear of failed or delayed deliveries due to high security risks. \par \par \uc2  Even more worrisome, is that the heightened security risks will consequently increase business risks. This, in turn, could cause more bad loans and turn newly restructured credits sour again, thereby threatening the fragile banking industry. \par \par \uc2  While businesses badly need loans to expand operations, many banks may become inordinately cautious about any new lending due to fears of worsening capital standards. \par \par \uc2  The negative market perception of the \b \highlight22\uc2 economic\b0 \highlight\uc2  outlook would also adversely affect the many reform measures that are badly needed to fuel a stronger recovery. The biggest toll may be in asset recovery and privatization as foreign investors could shun the country - at least until all the questions around the bomb attack are resolved. State-owned Bank Mandiri, for example, was immediately forced to postpone its initial \b \highlight22\uc2 public\b0 \highlight\uc2  offering and the divestment of many other state-owned assets became \b \highlight22\uc2 uncertain\b0 \highlight\uc2  amid the bearish market perception. \par \par \uc2  All these risks can only be overcome by stronger government leadership in taking decisive \b \highlight22\uc2 policy\b0 \highlight\uc2  action to accelerate the implementation of reform measures and to maintain \b \highlight22\uc2 policy\b0 \highlight\uc2  coherence. \par \par \uc2  Only a more rapid privatization and asset recovery, accelerated adoption of structural reform measures and more vigorous \b \highlight22\uc2 tax\b0 \highlight\uc2  collection can create a virtuous circle of increased market confidence, a stronger exchange rate and declining interest rate. \par \par \uc2  This is, for example, a critical and opportune time to make a firm decision on the restructuring of all small-and medium-scale business debtors to release them from the bondage of their debts and allow them to thrive in the open market. \par \par \uc2  But market confidence is vital because the wellsprings of \b \highlight22\uc2 economic\b0 \highlight\uc2  growth are not just technology, investment and consumer \b \highlight22\uc2 spending\b0 \highlight\uc2 . They also include the spirit of risk taking by entrepreneurs. \par \par \uc2  However, investors will not be willing to risk their capital in the absence of decisive \b \highlight22\uc2 policy\b0 \highlight\uc2  action on the part of the government. Only under strong government leadership, characterized by firm and consistent \b \highlight22\uc2 policy\b0 \highlight\uc2  action can businesses be confident enough to weather all the negative pressures from the heightened security risks, in order that they can be optimistic about the long-term outlook of the \b \highlight22\uc2 economy\b0 \highlight\uc2 . \par \par \uc2  Copyright 2002 The Jakarta Post. \par \par \uc2 Document jkpost0020021025dyap0000e\par }\page {\par\fs20{\*\shppict{\pict\pngblip\picw298\pich36\picscaley100\picscalex100\picwgoal4470\pichgoal540
