\par\par \b \uc2  Indonesian  \highlight22\uc2 economy \highlight\uc2  grew 3.92 percent in 3rd quarter - BPS. \b0\par\par\uc2 456 \uc2 words\par \uc2 16 November 2002\par \uc2 The Jakarta Post\par \uc2 JKPOST\par  2 \par \uc2 English\par \uc2 (c) 2002 The Jakarta Post\par \par \uc2  The Jakarta Post, Jakarta \par \par \uc2  The \b \highlight22\uc2 economy\b0 \highlight\uc2  grew by 3.92 percent during the third quarter over the same period last year, said the Central Bureau of Statistics (BPS), adding that slowing consumption growth meant Indonesia would be unlikely to meet its full year \b \highlight22\uc2 economic\b0 \highlight\uc2  growth target of 4 percent. \par \par \uc2  BPS deputy chairman La Ode Syafiuddin said on Friday that domestic consumption remained the key driver behind the 3.92 percent third quarter growth in the \b \highlight22\uc2 economy\b0 \highlight\uc2 . \par \par \uc2  "Although growth in private consumption has slowed down a bit, it has still contributed a lot to the overall \b \highlight22\uc2 economy\b0 \highlight\uc2 ," he told a press briefing. "Exports and investment also increased slightly." \par \par \uc2  Third quarter private consumption, as measured by household \b \highlight22\uc2 spending\b0 \highlight\uc2 , grew more slowly at 4.9 percent against 6.3 percent during the third quarter last year. \par \par \uc2  Over the same period, however, exports and investment \b \highlight22\uc2 spending\b0 \highlight\uc2  recovered after both had plunged in the second quarter. \par \par \uc2  Exports grew by 1.6 after slumping by 7.1 percent in the previous year, while investment grew by 2.1 percent compared to a 1 percent drop last year. \par \par \uc2  Despite the promising figures, Syafiuddin warned that the upward trend was unsustainable. \par \par \uc2  The BPS growth figures have yet to fully take account of the Oct. 12 Bali bombing, which will dampen the \b \highlight22\uc2 economic\b0 \highlight\uc2  outlook well into 2003. \par \par \uc2  The terrorist attack on the holiday island has dealt a severe blow to Indonesia's tourism sector, which on average contributes US$5 billion to the \b \highlight22\uc2 economy\b0 \highlight\uc2 . \par \par \uc2  Renewed security concerns also undermine business confidence in a country where the net capital inflow is already negative. \par \par \uc2  Legal \b \highlight22\uc2 uncertainties\b0 \highlight\uc2 , a corruption prone judiciary, and turbulent labor relations are among the main investor worries keeping capital away from the country. \par \par \uc2  The government has revised down its \b \highlight22\uc2 economic\b0 \highlight\uc2  growth target, as measured by the country's gross domestic product (GDP), to 4 percent from 5 percent previously. GDP measures the annual output of goods and services produced in a country. \par \par \uc2  Analysts, however, doubt that the revision is sufficient to reflect the \b \highlight22\uc2 economic\b0 \highlight\uc2  fallout from the Oct. 12 terrorist strike. \par \par \uc2  "The Bali bombings will certainly take their toll on the \b \highlight22\uc2 economy\b0 \highlight\uc2 . I don't have the precise figures, but it'll be impossible to achieve the 4 percent target (of growth)," Syafiuddin said. \par \par \uc2  Aviliani, an economist at the Institute for \b \highlight22\uc2 Economic\b0 \highlight\uc2  and Finance Development (Indef), was also doubtful about the target. \par \par \uc2  She said investment and exports needed to grow faster if the 4 percent growth target was to be achieved. \par \par \uc2  "Even before the Bali attacks, the performance of these two indicators have been somewhat disappointing. I think the target is no longer realistic at this stage," she said. \par \par \uc2  Copyright 2002 The Jakarta Post. \par \par \uc2 Document jkpost0020021116dybg00007\par }\page {\par\fs20{\*\shppict{\pict\pngblip\picw298\pich36\picscaley100\picscalex100\picwgoal4470\pichgoal540
