\par\par \b \uc2  Deliberation begins on new water bill. \b0\par\par\uc2 559 \uc2 words\par \uc2 25 November 2002\par \uc2 The Jakarta Post\par \uc2 JKPOST\par  4 \par \uc2 English\par \uc2 (c) 2002 The Jakarta Post\par \par \uc2  Moch. N. Kurniawan, The Jakarta Post, Jakarta \par \par \uc2  The government and the \b \highlight22\uc2 House of Representatives\b0 \highlight\uc2  have begun deliberating a bill on water resources, which they claim will ensure \b \highlight22\uc2 public\b0 \highlight\uc2  participation in determining the use of the resource as well as protecting people's right to water. \par \par \uc2  Minister of Resettlement and Regional Infrastructure Soenarno said the bill assumed the \b \highlight22\uc2 public\b0 \highlight\uc2  deserved a role in deciding the planning, execution, supervision and evaluation of the utilization of water. \par \par \uc2  He said, for example, that the bill detailed the need to establish a water resource council made up of ministries and other stakeholders, which would recommend \b \highlight22\uc2 policy\b0 \highlight\uc2  and strategy on water resources. \par \par \uc2  These councils would be established at the national, provincial and regency levels, according to draft bill. \par \par \uc2  If passed into law, the bill on water resources would replace Law No. 11/1974 on water. \par \par \uc2  Soenarno also said the government hoped to use the bill to protect the right of the powerless to access water; a right that is sometimes lost through the exploitation of the resource. \par \par \uc2  "The protection will combine social, \b \highlight22\uc2 economic\b0 \highlight\uc2  and environmental values, as water is a basic human need and it must be accessible to everyone," he said. \par \par \uc2  According to the minister, the bill clearly distinguishes between the functions of the central government and regional governments in handling water resources, in accordance with regional autonomy. \par \par \uc2  "The role of the central government will focus on water across provinces, and provincial administrations on water beyond the borders of regencies," he said. \par \par \uc2  The bill also ensures water conservation and threatens penalties to those who harm or pollute water resources, he said. \par \par \uc2  Sulaiman N. Sembiring, executive director of the Institute of Natural Resources Law, hailed the bill, saying it was more comprehensive than Law No. 11/1974. \par \par \uc2  However, he said the draft bill did not do enough to accommodate the voices of local stakeholders. \par \par \uc2  "Without the participation of local people expressing their problems, the bill will be fine in writing but unrealistic in practice. So don't discuss it only in Jakarta, but go to the provinces and regencies," he told The Jakarta Post. \par \par \uc2  Sulaiman also warned that the bill could provide private firms the opportunity to control water resources. \par \par \uc2  "We fear water resources will fall under the control of a few big firms and people will find it more and more difficult to access water," he said. \par \par \uc2  Regarding the penalties laid out in the draft, Sulaiman said those who damaged water resources should get more than a three-year jail sentence and a Rp 300 million fine, as stipulated in Article 93 of the bill. \par \par \uc2  "The environmental destruction resulting from the disruption of water resources is difficult to measure. The punishment is too light," he said. \par \par \uc2  Meanwhile, Riki F. Ibrahim, senior official at the Indonesian Geothermal Association, said the bill failed to clearly define water resources, thus raising the potential for dispute with other rulings and draft laws. \par \par \uc2  Citing an example, he said the bill on water resources conflicted with the bill on geothermal resources when it came to \b \highlight22\uc2 taxes\b0 \highlight\uc2 , which would cause legal \b \highlight22\uc2 uncertainty\b0 \highlight\uc2  among businesspeople. \par \par \uc2  "Under the geothermal bill, certain \b \highlight22\uc2 taxes\b0 \highlight\uc2  are imposed on geothermal businessmen, who will also be subject to \b \highlight22\uc2 taxes\b0 \highlight\uc2  according to the water resource bill. \par \par \uc2  "This water resources bill needs an overhaul before being endorsed," he said. \par \par \uc2  Copyright 2002 The Jakarta Post. \par \par \uc2 Document jkpost0020021124dybp0005r\par }\page {\par\fs20{\*\shppict{\pict\pngblip\picw298\pich36\picscaley100\picscalex100\picwgoal4470\pichgoal540
