\par\par \b \uc2  THURSDAY'S EDITORIALS FROM INDONESIAN DAILIES. \b0\par\par\uc2 414 \uc2 words\par \uc2 28 November 2002\par \uc2 LKBN ANTARA\par \uc2 ANTARA\par \uc2 English\par \uc2 (c) 2002 Asia Pulse Pte Limited. Asia Pulse gives no warranty or guarantee as to the accuracy of the information, Asia Pulse shall not be liable for errors or omissions in, or delays or interruptions to or cessation of delivery of, the data through its negligence or otherwise.\par \par \uc2  NEW 2003 \b \highlight22\uc2 BUDGET\b0 \highlight\uc2  APPROVED \par \par \uc2  The state \b \highlight22\uc2 budget\b0 \highlight\uc2  proposal for 2003 that was approved by the \b \highlight22\uc2 House of\b0 \highlight\b \highlight22\uc2 Representatives\b0 \highlight\uc2  on Wednesday was significantly different from the original plan submitted in August because of major changes in several key \b \highlight22\uc2 economic\b0 \highlight\uc2  assumptions brought about by the Oct. 12 bomb attack in Bali. \par \par \uc2  The target of \b \highlight22\uc2 economic\b0 \highlight\uc2  growth in terms of real gross domestic product was revised downward from 5 percent to 4 percent and the average rupiah rate from Rp8,700 to a range of between Rp8,500 and 9,500 relative to the U.S. dollar. \par \par \uc2  Most analyst have predicted that without an additional \b \highlight22\uc2 stimulus\b0 \highlight\uc2  the \b \highlight22\uc2 economy\b0 \highlight\uc2  would only be able to expand by a mere 3.5 percent at the most next year, or about similar to the estimated growth for this year. \par \par \uc2  True, the government should come up with additional pump priming measures to offset an anticipated slackening of the pace of private investment and consumer \b \highlight22\uc2 spending\b0 \highlight\uc2 , because the increased security risks and anticipated negative ramifications of the bomb attack on domestic political conditions are heightening business risks, adversely affecting business confidence and ba